{"_id":"7aeynG0ZDWA55cql","name":"Ambrose the Sorcerer known as Old Merlin","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"TvxxLoHTWNq5DO7o","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer known as Old Merlin","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient sorcerer, my body is weak, but my magical \npower is unmatched.\n1 Wound</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 45","positive":"I am an ancient sorcerer, my body is weak, but my magical \npower is unmatched.\n1 Wound","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer known as Old Merlin","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RlsBBGxp9O0En4FH","name":"Gift - Ancient Sorcerer","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer known as Old Merlin","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Merlin’s power is incredible, \nachieving practically anything he can think of through the \nuse of magic. Those who rely on his advice will be able, once \nper Session, to activate the magic power that the wizard has \ninfused within them. The magical effects must be decided \nat the time that Merlin blesses the character by defining an \nappropriate Descriptor such as: Taking flight like a bird or \nHaving skin as hard as a stone. Whoever carries Merlin’s \nmagic can activate its power once, obtaining the Descriptor \nfor the entire Scene. Once the Scene resolves the magic is \ndrained from the player and cannot be activated again.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 45","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer known as Old Merlin","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Nf1iPZTNDDDi7xkx","name":"Gift - Wise Advice","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer known as Old Merlin","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Merlin will never intervene \npersonally but can appear in a dream or vision to his \nprotégés. Once per Scenario, a Hunter can spend 1 Soma \nto summon Merlin’s help. The sorcerer will appear with \nhelpful information or to bless the character with one of \nhis spells.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 45","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer known as Old Merlin","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"okxv5keBrqoFtIbR","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer known as Old Merlin","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Ambrose the Sorcerer \nknown as Old Merlin\nInspired by Merlin from the Arthurian Myth (Neutral)\nDeep mysteries still surround wielders of magic and their secret, \ncenturies-old struggle for control of the arcane world. Some legends tell \nof the two most outstanding practitioners of arcane arts: Baba Yaga, the \nwitch forced into the body of a child, and Ambrose, constrained into \nthe body of a tired old man. Under the false name of Merlin, Ambrose \nhas been pulling the strings of humanity’s destiny for centuries. He \npretends to be of service to those who need him most, while in truth his \nactions only strengthen his position. Many seek the old hermit Merlin for \nadvice or help, unaware that the only support he dispenses is that which \nsupports himself. With each new petitioner, the ancient sorcerer grows \never closer to absolute power.\nDescriptor: I am an ancient sorcerer, my body is weak, but my magical \npower is unmatched.\n1 Wound \nOpposition Level: Hard 7 \nAgenda: Pretending to be a wise old man who is always ready to \nhelp others with the proper advice / Gaining personal advantage by \nmanipulating others. \nSpecial Agenda (Baba Yaga): I both respect and hate Yaga. \nHers is the only power that can stand against mine. While the laws of \nmagic prevent me from killing her directly, nothing prevents me from \nmaneuvering her into danger. And if she perishes due to her own \nfoolishness, all the better.\n45\nSpecial Agenda (Morgana of the Lake): I fear the \npower of the greatest sorceress of all time. Thanks to an \nagreement with Baba Yaga, we have sealed the memory of \nyoung Morgana. I will do whatever it takes to keep her from \nawakening.\nNote: Morgana of the Lake is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I respect \nMarina as a skilled witch and I seek her aid against Baba \nYaga. Obviously, once my great enemy is defeated, I will have \nto make sure that Marina does not take her place.\nGift – Ancient Sorcerer: Merlin’s power is incredible, \nachieving practically anything he can think of through the \nuse of magic. Those who rely on his advice will be able, once \nper Session, to activate the magic power that the wizard has \ninfused within them. The magical effects must be decided \nat the time that Merlin blesses the character by defining an \nappropriate Descriptor such as: Taking flight like a bird or \nHaving skin as hard as a stone. Whoever carries Merlin’s \nmagic can activate its power once, obtaining the Descriptor \nfor the entire Scene. Once the Scene resolves the magic is \ndrained from the player and cannot be activated again.\nGift – Wise Advice: Merlin will never intervene \npersonally but can appear in a dream or vision to his \nprotégés. Once per Scenario, a Hunter can spend 1 Soma \nto summon Merlin’s help. The sorcerer will appear with \nhelpful information or to bless the character with one of \nhis spells.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 45","owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer known as Old Merlin","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-ambrose-the-sorcerer-known-as-old-merlin-45","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":45}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Ambrose the Sorcerer \nknown as Old Merlin\nInspired by Merlin from the Arthurian Myth (Neutral)\nDeep mysteries still surround wielders of magic and their secret, \ncenturies-old struggle for control of the arcane world. Some legends tell \nof the two most outstanding practitioners of arcane arts: Baba Yaga, the \nwitch forced into the body of a child, and Ambrose, constrained into \nthe body of a tired old man. Under the false name of Merlin, Ambrose \nhas been pulling the strings of humanity’s destiny for centuries. He \npretends to be of service to those who need him most, while in truth his \nactions only strengthen his position. Many seek the old hermit Merlin for \nadvice or help, unaware that the only support he dispenses is that which \nsupports himself. With each new petitioner, the ancient sorcerer grows \never closer to absolute power.\nDescriptor: I am an ancient sorcerer, my body is weak, but my magical \npower is unmatched.\n1 Wound \nOpposition Level: Hard 7 \nAgenda: Pretending to be a wise old man who is always ready to \nhelp others with the proper advice / Gaining personal advantage by \nmanipulating others. \nSpecial Agenda (Baba Yaga): I both respect and hate Yaga. \nHers is the only power that can stand against mine. While the laws of \nmagic prevent me from killing her directly, nothing prevents me from \nmaneuvering her into danger. And if she perishes due to her own \nfoolishness, all the better.\n45\nSpecial Agenda (Morgana of the Lake): I fear the \npower of the greatest sorceress of all time. Thanks to an \nagreement with Baba Yaga, we have sealed the memory of \nyoung Morgana. I will do whatever it takes to keep her from \nawakening.\nNote: Morgana of the Lake is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I respect \nMarina as a skilled witch and I seek her aid against Baba \nYaga. Obviously, once my great enemy is defeated, I will have \nto make sure that Marina does not take her place.\nGift – Ancient Sorcerer: Merlin’s power is incredible, \nachieving practically anything he can think of through the \nuse of magic. Those who rely on his advice will be able, once \nper Session, to activate the magic power that the wizard has \ninfused within them. The magical effects must be decided \nat the time that Merlin blesses the character by defining an \nappropriate Descriptor such as: Taking flight like a bird or \nHaving skin as hard as a stone. Whoever carries Merlin’s \nmagic can activate its power once, obtaining the Descriptor \nfor the entire Scene. Once the Scene resolves the magic is \ndrained from the player and cannot be activated again.\nGift – Wise Advice: Merlin will never intervene \npersonally but can appear in a dream or vision to his \nprotégés. Once per Scenario, a Hunter can spend 1 Soma \nto summon Merlin’s help. The sorcerer will appear with \nhelpful information or to bless the character with one of \nhis spells.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Pretending to be a wise old man who is always ready to \nhelp others with the proper advice / Gaining personal advantage by \nmanipulating others. \nSpecial Agenda (Baba Yaga): I both respect and hate Yaga. \nHers is the only power that can stand against mine. While the laws of \nmagic prevent me from killing her directly, nothing prevents me from \nmaneuvering her into danger. And if she perishes due to her own \nfoolishness, all the better.\n45\nSpecial Agenda (Morgana of the Lake): I fear the \npower of the greatest sorceress of all time. Thanks to an \nagreement with Baba Yaga, we have sealed the memory of \nyoung Morgana. I will do whatever it takes to keep her from \nawakening.\nNote: Morgana of the Lake is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I respect \nMarina as a skilled witch and I seek her aid against Baba \nYaga. Obviously, once my great enemy is defeated, I will have \nto make sure that Marina does not take her place.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9zJlWopyWT61SauX","name":"Frog Face","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"irga8bc2xsHwcr0w","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a wealthy, deformed noble, using my \nresources to achieve my purposes.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 46","positive":"I am a wealthy, deformed noble, using my \nresources to achieve my purposes.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lpbVoOYJHEJ71WJ7","name":"Gift - By Any Means","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Frog Face’s only desire is to break \nthe “curse” that afflicts him. When he is trying to obtain \nsomething that obviously brings him closer to his goal, his \nOpposition Level becomes Hard 7.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 46","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fMYAMVkoJnHdb9mS","name":"Gift - True Love’s Kiss","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>After years of experimental \nmedicine, Frog Face’s saliva has acquired strange attributes. \nWhoever is kissed or licked by Frog Face will go into a daze \nfor the rest of the Scene, lowering their Opposition Level \nby 2 (in the case of an NPC) or receiving 2 Penalties at \neach Check (in the case of a Hunter). A Hunter can make a \nDefense Check to resist the effects of True Love’s Kiss.\nHeinrich the Trustworthy</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 46","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7NoKedpFfMeMQ6OO","name":"Gift - Legendary Warrior","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The \nSword Demon’s prowess is unmatched. \nDuring the course of a Scene, an \nenemy will not be able to use the same \nGift twice against the Sword Demon. \nHaving seen them in action once, \nthe Demon will always find a way to \nanticipate the enemy and counter \ntheir strategy.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 46","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wIUo6dwLVkdtL878","name":"Gift - The Demon Blade","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Any \nedged weapon wielded by the Sword \nDemon becomes lethal. With her \nweapon, the Demon can cut through \nsolid objects, stop arrows, and even \ndispel magic. Thanks to her iron will, \nthe Sword Demon can defend herself \nagainst any type of attack, canceling \nthe narrative advantage given by any \nassociated Descriptors.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 46","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"GWXKbUson2JUZa8C","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Frog Face\nInspired by The Frog Prince (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, the heir of a noble family was born \ndeformed. His face was broad and covered with pustules, his \neyes huge and yellow, and his skin a frog-like green. Destroyed \nby grief, the young man’s mother wished to keep him hidden \nfrom the world until he came of age. However, his father’s \nuntimely death made him the new head of the family. Locked \nin a world of fairytales and lies by his mother, the young scion \nwas convinced that he was the victim of a curse that only a \nkiss from someone truly in love could break. For years, Frog \nFace tried to find love and break the spell, receiving in return \nonly rejection and contempt. On the verge of madness, Frog \nFace decided that if he couldn’t have true love, he would take \nsomeone else’s. Since that day, Frog Face travels accompanied \nby his trusty servant Heinrich. The two spy on people and \nwhen they find a couple in love, they kidnap one of the two \nlovers to snatch a kiss. This perpetuates a vicious circle of hope \nand disappointment that always culminates in the killing of \nthose who, in the eyes of Frog Face, do not nurture a love pure \nenough to break the curse.\nDescriptor: I am a wealthy, deformed noble, using my \nresources to achieve my purposes.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: Find someone truly in love and force them to kiss \nme to regain a normal appearance.\n46\nGift - By Any Means: Frog Face’s only desire is to break \nthe “curse” that afflicts him. When he is trying to obtain \nsomething that obviously brings him closer to his goal, his \nOpposition Level becomes Hard 7.\nGift - True Love’s Kiss: After years of experimental \nmedicine, Frog Face’s saliva has acquired strange attributes. \nWhoever is kissed or licked by Frog Face will go into a daze \nfor the rest of the Scene, lowering their Opposition Level \nby 2 (in the case of an NPC) or receiving 2 Penalties at \neach Check (in the case of a Hunter). A Hunter can make a \nDefense Check to resist the effects of True Love’s Kiss.\nHeinrich the Trustworthy\nDescriptor: I am the old family coachman, the only one \nwho knows the truth about my master. Over time, the grief \nfor his fate has driven me mad.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: To help my lord realize his crazy dream, preserving \nhim from a truth he would not accept.\n47\nOnce upon a time, there was a young \ngirl who lived in the Far East. When \nthey drafted her old father for war, \nthe young woman pretended to be a \nboy to take his place, as women were \nnot allowed to be soldiers at the time. \nUnder the false name of Hua Mulan, \nthe young warrior won every battle \nand brought glory to her army, but \nwhen her true identity was discovered, \nenvious generals took advantage of it to \naccuse her of deception and betrayal. \nBranded and exiled, the warrior fled \nher home, eventually reaching Europe \nafter a long and wandering journey. \nTired and embittered at finding the \nsame sort of injustice wherever she \nwent, Hua Mulan decided she would \nrun no more. She made a disguise of her \nancestral armor, hiding her face behind \nthe features of a snarling demon. Under \nthe name of the Sword Demon, the \nwarrior now wanders around Europe, \nwielding her blade against everything \nthat represents the status quo, such as \nthe Order itself.\nDescriptor: I am a skilled warrior \nand have won a thousand battles. I hate \ninjustice and I know that the way of the \nsword is the only answer.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Hard 7\nAgenda: Punishing injustice and \nrighting wrongs using the only tongue \nthe vile can understand – the language \nof the blade / Deep in my heart I hope \nto find someone who can show me what \ntrue justice is.\nGift - Legendary Warrior: The \nSword Demon’s prowess is unmatched. \nDuring the course of a Scene, an \nenemy will not be able to use the same \nGift twice against the Sword Demon. \nHaving seen them in action once, \nthe Demon will always find a way to \nanticipate the enemy and counter \ntheir strategy.\nGift - The Demon Blade: Any \nedged weapon wielded by the Sword \nDemon becomes lethal. With her \nweapon, the Demon can cut through \nsolid objects, stop arrows, and even \ndispel magic. Thanks to her iron will, \nthe Sword Demon can defend herself \nagainst any type of attack, canceling \nthe narrative advantage given by any \nassociated Descriptors.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 46","owner":"Frog Face","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-frog-face-46","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":46}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Frog Face\nInspired by The Frog Prince (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, the heir of a noble family was born \ndeformed. His face was broad and covered with pustules, his \neyes huge and yellow, and his skin a frog-like green. Destroyed \nby grief, the young man’s mother wished to keep him hidden \nfrom the world until he came of age. However, his father’s \nuntimely death made him the new head of the family. Locked \nin a world of fairytales and lies by his mother, the young scion \nwas convinced that he was the victim of a curse that only a \nkiss from someone truly in love could break. For years, Frog \nFace tried to find love and break the spell, receiving in return \nonly rejection and contempt. On the verge of madness, Frog \nFace decided that if he couldn’t have true love, he would take \nsomeone else’s. Since that day, Frog Face travels accompanied \nby his trusty servant Heinrich. The two spy on people and \nwhen they find a couple in love, they kidnap one of the two \nlovers to snatch a kiss. This perpetuates a vicious circle of hope \nand disappointment that always culminates in the killing of \nthose who, in the eyes of Frog Face, do not nurture a love pure \nenough to break the curse.\nDescriptor: I am a wealthy, deformed noble, using my \nresources to achieve my purposes.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: Find someone truly in love and force them to kiss \nme to regain a normal appearance.\n46\nGift - By Any Means: Frog Face’s only desire is to break \nthe “curse” that afflicts him. When he is trying to obtain \nsomething that obviously brings him closer to his goal, his \nOpposition Level becomes Hard 7.\nGift - True Love’s Kiss: After years of experimental \nmedicine, Frog Face’s saliva has acquired strange attributes. \nWhoever is kissed or licked by Frog Face will go into a daze \nfor the rest of the Scene, lowering their Opposition Level \nby 2 (in the case of an NPC) or receiving 2 Penalties at \neach Check (in the case of a Hunter). A Hunter can make a \nDefense Check to resist the effects of True Love’s Kiss.\nHeinrich the Trustworthy\nDescriptor: I am the old family coachman, the only one \nwho knows the truth about my master. Over time, the grief \nfor his fate has driven me mad.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: To help my lord realize his crazy dream, preserving \nhim from a truth he would not accept.\n47\nOnce upon a time, there was a young \ngirl who lived in the Far East. When \nthey drafted her old father for war, \nthe young woman pretended to be a \nboy to take his place, as women were \nnot allowed to be soldiers at the time. \nUnder the false name of Hua Mulan, \nthe young warrior won every battle \nand brought glory to her army, but \nwhen her true identity was discovered, \nenvious generals took advantage of it to \naccuse her of deception and betrayal. \nBranded and exiled, the warrior fled \nher home, eventually reaching Europe \nafter a long and wandering journey. \nTired and embittered at finding the \nsame sort of injustice wherever she \nwent, Hua Mulan decided she would \nrun no more. She made a disguise of her \nancestral armor, hiding her face behind \nthe features of a snarling demon. Under \nthe name of the Sword Demon, the \nwarrior now wanders around Europe, \nwielding her blade against everything \nthat represents the status quo, such as \nthe Order itself.\nDescriptor: I am a skilled warrior \nand have won a thousand battles. I hate \ninjustice and I know that the way of the \nsword is the only answer.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Hard 7\nAgenda: Punishing injustice and \nrighting wrongs using the only tongue \nthe vile can understand – the language \nof the blade / Deep in my heart I hope \nto find someone who can show me what \ntrue justice is.\nGift - Legendary Warrior: The \nSword Demon’s prowess is unmatched. \nDuring the course of a Scene, an \nenemy will not be able to use the same \nGift twice against the Sword Demon. \nHaving seen them in action once, \nthe Demon will always find a way to \nanticipate the enemy and counter \ntheir strategy.\nGift - The Demon Blade: Any \nedged weapon wielded by the Sword \nDemon becomes lethal. With her \nweapon, the Demon can cut through \nsolid objects, stop arrows, and even \ndispel magic. Thanks to her iron will, \nthe Sword Demon can defend herself \nagainst any type of attack, canceling \nthe narrative advantage given by any \nassociated Descriptors.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Find someone truly in love and force them to kiss \nme to regain a normal appearance.\n46","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wRVmA64AKafaXHfi","name":"The Periwinkle Peer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"UUQvVkqPBNH58k58","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the best \nat everything I do and I must \nwin every challenge. I do not \nexcel in science and academic \nknowledge, but no one must \ndiscover this weakness of mine. I prefer to show off my \nphysical prowess and skill.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 49","positive":"I am the best \nat everything I do and I must \nwin every challenge. I do not \nexcel in science and academic \nknowledge, but no one must \ndiscover this weakness of mine. I prefer to show off my \nphysical prowess and skill.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QYtLLQmRTY1WPKue","name":"Gift - Obsession for Perfection","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Periwinkle Peer \ndraws strength from the drive to win every challenge. When \nan enemy succeeds in a Defense Check against his action, \nthe Peer gets +1 to his Opposition Level for the rest of the \nScene. This bonus is cumulative. Once per Scene, when the \nPeer receives his final Wound, he will mock his enemy \nin a fit of rage and grit his teeth to keep from being \nknocked out, immediately recovering 1 Wound.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 49","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"naigfXvfLUjM3YQX","name":"Gift - Divine Charm","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Periwinkle Peer \npossesses good looks and charm out of \nthe ordinary. With his mere presence, \nhe is able to beguile anyone. During \na Scene in which he is present, the \nStoryteller can create an Agenda \nfor a Minor NPC that describes \ntheir infatuation with the Peer. \nThis Agenda is more important \nthan all of the NPC’s past ties, and \nalso any pacts they might have \nstruck with the Hunters. The Peer \ncan also influence Major NPCs (at \nthe Storyteller’s discretion) or a \nHunter. In this case, the Player will \ncreate a Descriptor that represents\n49\nhow The Periwinkle Peer impressed the Hunter. This \nnew Descriptor lasts until the next Interlude and can be \nmarked as usual to get XP .</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 49","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fpq9ST38h9IERE1w","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Periwinkle Peer\nInspired by Prince Charming (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a handsome nobleman born \nthe heir to a wealthy family. The Young Lord was famous \nfor his prized, periwinkle blue cloak, which would catch \nevery eye whenever he entered a room. But despite everyone’s \nadmiration and every young woman claiming him as a lover, \nthe lordling was obsessed with only one thing: perfection. The \nYoung Lord’s parents were the only ones who knew of their \nson’s bedeviling compulsion, which in the past had \ndriven him to kill his brother, executed for the \ncrime of being a better horseman. Blinded by love, \nthe Young Lord’s parents pushed him into a \nmilitary career. The Young Lord rose through \nthe ranks quickly, driven as he ever was to \nexcel. Then, he learned of sordid intrigues \nthat could be used to garner preferment \nand promotion. His madness \nresurfaced, eventually driving him to \nmurder once more. A wanted man \nand a deserter, today the Young \nLord wanders endlessly, always \nlooking for challenges to prove \nhis superiority, putting himself \nat the service of anyone who \npraises his perfection.\nDescriptor: I am the best \nat everything I do and I must \nwin every challenge. I do not \nexcel in science and academic \nknowledge, but no one must \ndiscover this weakness of mine. I prefer to show off my \nphysical prowess and skill.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5 \nAgenda: I must prove my perfection, even if it means \ndrowning doubters in blood.\nGift - Obsession for Perfection: The Periwinkle Peer \ndraws strength from the drive to win every challenge. When \nan enemy succeeds in a Defense Check against his action, \nthe Peer gets +1 to his Opposition Level for the rest of the \nScene. This bonus is cumulative. Once per Scene, when the \nPeer receives his final Wound, he will mock his enemy \nin a fit of rage and grit his teeth to keep from being \nknocked out, immediately recovering 1 Wound.\nGift - Divine Charm: The Periwinkle Peer \npossesses good looks and charm out of \nthe ordinary. With his mere presence, \nhe is able to beguile anyone. During \na Scene in which he is present, the \nStoryteller can create an Agenda \nfor a Minor NPC that describes \ntheir infatuation with the Peer. \nThis Agenda is more important \nthan all of the NPC’s past ties, and \nalso any pacts they might have \nstruck with the Hunters. The Peer \ncan also influence Major NPCs (at \nthe Storyteller’s discretion) or a \nHunter. In this case, the Player will \ncreate a Descriptor that represents\n49\nhow The Periwinkle Peer impressed the Hunter. This \nnew Descriptor lasts until the next Interlude and can be \nmarked as usual to get XP .</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 49","owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-periwinkle-peer-49","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":49}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Periwinkle Peer\nInspired by Prince Charming (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a handsome nobleman born \nthe heir to a wealthy family. The Young Lord was famous \nfor his prized, periwinkle blue cloak, which would catch \nevery eye whenever he entered a room. But despite everyone’s \nadmiration and every young woman claiming him as a lover, \nthe lordling was obsessed with only one thing: perfection. The \nYoung Lord’s parents were the only ones who knew of their \nson’s bedeviling compulsion, which in the past had \ndriven him to kill his brother, executed for the \ncrime of being a better horseman. Blinded by love, \nthe Young Lord’s parents pushed him into a \nmilitary career. The Young Lord rose through \nthe ranks quickly, driven as he ever was to \nexcel. Then, he learned of sordid intrigues \nthat could be used to garner preferment \nand promotion. His madness \nresurfaced, eventually driving him to \nmurder once more. A wanted man \nand a deserter, today the Young \nLord wanders endlessly, always \nlooking for challenges to prove \nhis superiority, putting himself \nat the service of anyone who \npraises his perfection.\nDescriptor: I am the best \nat everything I do and I must \nwin every challenge. I do not \nexcel in science and academic \nknowledge, but no one must \ndiscover this weakness of mine. I prefer to show off my \nphysical prowess and skill.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5 \nAgenda: I must prove my perfection, even if it means \ndrowning doubters in blood.\nGift - Obsession for Perfection: The Periwinkle Peer \ndraws strength from the drive to win every challenge. When \nan enemy succeeds in a Defense Check against his action, \nthe Peer gets +1 to his Opposition Level for the rest of the \nScene. This bonus is cumulative. Once per Scene, when the \nPeer receives his final Wound, he will mock his enemy \nin a fit of rage and grit his teeth to keep from being \nknocked out, immediately recovering 1 Wound.\nGift - Divine Charm: The Periwinkle Peer \npossesses good looks and charm out of \nthe ordinary. With his mere presence, \nhe is able to beguile anyone. During \na Scene in which he is present, the \nStoryteller can create an Agenda \nfor a Minor NPC that describes \ntheir infatuation with the Peer. \nThis Agenda is more important \nthan all of the NPC’s past ties, and \nalso any pacts they might have \nstruck with the Hunters. The Peer \ncan also influence Major NPCs (at \nthe Storyteller’s discretion) or a \nHunter. In this case, the Player will \ncreate a Descriptor that represents\n49\nhow The Periwinkle Peer impressed the Hunter. This \nnew Descriptor lasts until the next Interlude and can be \nmarked as usual to get XP .</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I must prove my perfection, even if it means \ndrowning doubters in blood.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IoATgZk5EvPxEOP7","name":"The Ancient Enemy","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"RYeVZGjy6P6iEawt","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Ancient Enemy","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient and powerful creature. \nMy body was formed in the fires of creation and common \nweapons can do nothing against me.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 50","positive":"I am an ancient and powerful creature. \nMy body was formed in the fires of creation and common \nweapons can do nothing against me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Ancient Enemy","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8N7l1bFmV9poYbvc","name":"Gift - Colossal Body","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Ancient Enemy","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Draco possesses a colossal body \nand is capable of flying at great speed. During a Scene \nor Exchange, he can act 3 times instead of once: with his \npowerful bite, with his front legs, and with his long tail. \nDraco’s strength is so great that each of his actions inflicts \n1 additional Wound. Finally, Draco can spit flames from \nhis mouth once per Scene, making an area attack in front \nof him, engulfing everything in flames.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 50","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Ancient Enemy","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"X7gmtGIFWqjdb3jL","name":"Gift - The Power of the Myth","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Ancient Enemy","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Draco is one of the \nmost powerful beings of any myth and, in the course \nof a Scene, he can use the following powers at will: 1. \nShapeshifter: Take on the appearance of an ordinary \nhuman or an animal. 2. Magicbreaker: Immediately \ncancel the effect of a spell or arcane object that has been \nused in his presence (the user can attempt a Defense \nCheck to avoid the effect of this power). 3. Gift of the \nDragon: Shed a piece of his body, such as a scale or a tooth, \nwhich can be used to forge objects with extraordinary \npowers.\n50</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 50","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Ancient Enemy","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Cc14IiyBqwOTdZLy","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Ancient Enemy","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Ancient Enemy\nInspired by the Dragon (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there lived an ancient and mighty \ncreature who had been a witness to the world’s unfolding \nsince time immemorial. Frightened mortals called it Draco, \nfearing its proud bearing and immeasurable power. But \ndespite his fearsome appearance, Draco wasn’t evil, just \ncurious. In hopes of creating another of his kind, as he \nhad watched countless mortals do, Draco laid an egg once \nevery century. Each time, evil and unscrupulous men took \npossession of it before it could be hatched, leaving him \nalone. After a thousand years, despair stole Draco’s ability \nto lay more eggs. The bitter truth was, to lay an egg was to \ncondemn it to an evil fate. Even today, it is said that Draco \nkeeps waiting for a person with a pure soul, able to show \nkindness and compassion enough to warm his heart, thereby \ngiving him hope for the future. Meanwhile, the lying legends \nof a great dragon, an ancient Enemy of mortals, have \nspread, reinforced by self-serving tales grown into myths \nand superstitions. More and more fools seek glory by setting \nout in search of the Ancient Enemy, invoking the grace of \nGod’s protection, to slay the legend once and for all.\nDescriptor: I am an ancient and powerful creature. \nMy body was formed in the fires of creation and common \nweapons can do nothing against me.\n6 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Hard 7 \nAgenda: To live in solitude and avoid contact with \nhumans, even if deep in my heart I still want to believe that \nthere is a mortal worthy of my respect.\nSpecial Agenda (St. George the Dragon Slayer): I \nhate St. George because he is a symbol of those who judge \nothers blindly, overawed by faith. I want to humiliate him \nand make those who believe in him see St. George as the \nlowest of the low.\nGift - Colossal Body: Draco possesses a colossal body \nand is capable of flying at great speed. During a Scene \nor Exchange, he can act 3 times instead of once: with his \npowerful bite, with his front legs, and with his long tail. \nDraco’s strength is so great that each of his actions inflicts \n1 additional Wound. Finally, Draco can spit flames from \nhis mouth once per Scene, making an area attack in front \nof him, engulfing everything in flames.\nGift – The Power of the Myth: Draco is one of the \nmost powerful beings of any myth and, in the course \nof a Scene, he can use the following powers at will: 1. \nShapeshifter: Take on the appearance of an ordinary \nhuman or an animal. 2. Magicbreaker: Immediately \ncancel the effect of a spell or arcane object that has been \nused in his presence (the user can attempt a Defense \nCheck to avoid the effect of this power). 3. Gift of the \nDragon: Shed a piece of his body, such as a scale or a tooth, \nwhich can be used to forge objects with extraordinary \npowers.\n50</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 50","owner":"The Ancient Enemy","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-ancient-enemy-50","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":50}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Ancient Enemy\nInspired by the Dragon (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there lived an ancient and mighty \ncreature who had been a witness to the world’s unfolding \nsince time immemorial. Frightened mortals called it Draco, \nfearing its proud bearing and immeasurable power. But \ndespite his fearsome appearance, Draco wasn’t evil, just \ncurious. In hopes of creating another of his kind, as he \nhad watched countless mortals do, Draco laid an egg once \nevery century. Each time, evil and unscrupulous men took \npossession of it before it could be hatched, leaving him \nalone. After a thousand years, despair stole Draco’s ability \nto lay more eggs. The bitter truth was, to lay an egg was to \ncondemn it to an evil fate. Even today, it is said that Draco \nkeeps waiting for a person with a pure soul, able to show \nkindness and compassion enough to warm his heart, thereby \ngiving him hope for the future. Meanwhile, the lying legends \nof a great dragon, an ancient Enemy of mortals, have \nspread, reinforced by self-serving tales grown into myths \nand superstitions. More and more fools seek glory by setting \nout in search of the Ancient Enemy, invoking the grace of \nGod’s protection, to slay the legend once and for all.\nDescriptor: I am an ancient and powerful creature. \nMy body was formed in the fires of creation and common \nweapons can do nothing against me.\n6 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Hard 7 \nAgenda: To live in solitude and avoid contact with \nhumans, even if deep in my heart I still want to believe that \nthere is a mortal worthy of my respect.\nSpecial Agenda (St. George the Dragon Slayer): I \nhate St. George because he is a symbol of those who judge \nothers blindly, overawed by faith. I want to humiliate him \nand make those who believe in him see St. George as the \nlowest of the low.\nGift - Colossal Body: Draco possesses a colossal body \nand is capable of flying at great speed. During a Scene \nor Exchange, he can act 3 times instead of once: with his \npowerful bite, with his front legs, and with his long tail. \nDraco’s strength is so great that each of his actions inflicts \n1 additional Wound. Finally, Draco can spit flames from \nhis mouth once per Scene, making an area attack in front \nof him, engulfing everything in flames.\nGift – The Power of the Myth: Draco is one of the \nmost powerful beings of any myth and, in the course \nof a Scene, he can use the following powers at will: 1. \nShapeshifter: Take on the appearance of an ordinary \nhuman or an animal. 2. Magicbreaker: Immediately \ncancel the effect of a spell or arcane object that has been \nused in his presence (the user can attempt a Defense \nCheck to avoid the effect of this power). 3. Gift of the \nDragon: Shed a piece of his body, such as a scale or a tooth, \nwhich can be used to forge objects with extraordinary \npowers.\n50</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"To live in solitude and avoid contact with \nhumans, even if deep in my heart I still want to believe that \nthere is a mortal worthy of my respect.\nSpecial Agenda (St. George the Dragon Slayer): I \nhate St. George because he is a symbol of those who judge \nothers blindly, overawed by faith. I want to humiliate him \nand make those who believe in him see St. George as the \nlowest of the low.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XRvbSbXEZVCzUI8m","name":"The Wild Swans Gang","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"zuAUFcQyVvN32Oq2","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a band of brothers and we specialize in fighting the \nOrder’s emissaries. Thanks to the curse that has been inflicted on us, we can \ntransform into swans.\n1 Wound (for each of the 11 gang members)</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 51","positive":"We are a band of brothers and we specialize in fighting the \nOrder’s emissaries. Thanks to the curse that has been inflicted on us, we can \ntransform into swans.\n1 Wound (for each of the 11 gang members)","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nvWegULOe5vVRbWV","name":"Gift - Change into a Swan","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A member of the Wild \nSwans Gang can transform into a swan at will. The \ntransformation is immediate. When it happens, it gives him \nthe new Descriptor: I am a wild swan – I can fly well, but \nI maintain my human consciousness. The gang member’s \nclothing, items, and other possessions are never lost during \nthe transformation.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 51","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vwOWaBXJuym72EhD","name":"Gift - The Swans Gang","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>When a member of the gang \nacts and has at least one partner to support him, he \nincreases his Opposition Level by 1. If at least 3 members \nfocus on supporting the same action, whoever performs it \nincreases the Opposition Level by 3 points.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 51","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8UfRk6GdgByj0bue","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Wild Swans Gang\nInspired by the Wild Swans (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there were eleven bold brothers, sons of an amiable \nnobleman. All were deeply attached to their younger sister Elisa and treated \nher like a queen. When the father remarried, the new wife, jealous of all the \nattention that the family reserved for Elisa, made a pact with Morgana, the \nfamous witch, to cast a powerful curse. The brothers were turned into swans \nand Elisa was blamed for it. Accused of being a sorcerer and cast out by \nher father, Elisa wandered for months looking for a new home. Finally, she \nreached another region, where she was welcomed by a local noble who soon \nfell in love with her beauty. Elisa began living happily, regularly meeting her \nbrothers, who in the meantime had been looking for a way to break the curse \ncast upon them. Elisa started to study magic to help them, but this attracted \nthe attention of the prelate of the country who, fearing the worst, requested \nthe Order’s intervention. Upon reaching Elisa’s presence, the Hunters noted \nher propensity for magic and took her away, turning her over to the papal \ninquisitors. When the eleven brothers found out, they cried bitter tears for \ntheir sister’s fate and swore revenge against the Order, waging war in the hope \nof finding Elisa alive.\nDescriptor: We are a band of brothers and we specialize in fighting the \nOrder’s emissaries. Thanks to the curse that has been inflicted on us, we can \ntransform into swans.\n1 Wound (for each of the 11 gang members)\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\n51\nAgenda: Defeat the Hunters of the Order and find Elisa / \nSave Elisa from the clutches of the Order, even if it means \ndestroying it.\nSpecial Agenda (Morgana of the Lake): We learned \nthat everything that happened to us is the fault of Morgana \nthe Witch, so we want to kidnap and force her to save Elisa \nwith her magic.\nNote: Morgana of the Lake is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\nGift – Change into a Swan: A member of the Wild \nSwans Gang can transform into a swan at will. The \ntransformation is immediate. When it happens, it gives him \nthe new Descriptor: I am a wild swan – I can fly well, but \nI maintain my human consciousness. The gang member’s \nclothing, items, and other possessions are never lost during \nthe transformation.\nGift – The Swans Gang: When a member of the gang \nacts and has at least one partner to support him, he \nincreases his Opposition Level by 1. If at least 3 members \nfocus on supporting the same action, whoever performs it \nincreases the Opposition Level by 3 points.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 51","owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-wild-swans-gang-51","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":51}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Wild Swans Gang\nInspired by the Wild Swans (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there were eleven bold brothers, sons of an amiable \nnobleman. All were deeply attached to their younger sister Elisa and treated \nher like a queen. When the father remarried, the new wife, jealous of all the \nattention that the family reserved for Elisa, made a pact with Morgana, the \nfamous witch, to cast a powerful curse. The brothers were turned into swans \nand Elisa was blamed for it. Accused of being a sorcerer and cast out by \nher father, Elisa wandered for months looking for a new home. Finally, she \nreached another region, where she was welcomed by a local noble who soon \nfell in love with her beauty. Elisa began living happily, regularly meeting her \nbrothers, who in the meantime had been looking for a way to break the curse \ncast upon them. Elisa started to study magic to help them, but this attracted \nthe attention of the prelate of the country who, fearing the worst, requested \nthe Order’s intervention. Upon reaching Elisa’s presence, the Hunters noted \nher propensity for magic and took her away, turning her over to the papal \ninquisitors. When the eleven brothers found out, they cried bitter tears for \ntheir sister’s fate and swore revenge against the Order, waging war in the hope \nof finding Elisa alive.\nDescriptor: We are a band of brothers and we specialize in fighting the \nOrder’s emissaries. Thanks to the curse that has been inflicted on us, we can \ntransform into swans.\n1 Wound (for each of the 11 gang members)\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\n51\nAgenda: Defeat the Hunters of the Order and find Elisa / \nSave Elisa from the clutches of the Order, even if it means \ndestroying it.\nSpecial Agenda (Morgana of the Lake): We learned \nthat everything that happened to us is the fault of Morgana \nthe Witch, so we want to kidnap and force her to save Elisa \nwith her magic.\nNote: Morgana of the Lake is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\nGift – Change into a Swan: A member of the Wild \nSwans Gang can transform into a swan at will. The \ntransformation is immediate. When it happens, it gives him \nthe new Descriptor: I am a wild swan – I can fly well, but \nI maintain my human consciousness. The gang member’s \nclothing, items, and other possessions are never lost during \nthe transformation.\nGift – The Swans Gang: When a member of the gang \nacts and has at least one partner to support him, he \nincreases his Opposition Level by 1. If at least 3 members \nfocus on supporting the same action, whoever performs it \nincreases the Opposition Level by 3 points.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defeat the Hunters of the Order and find Elisa / \nSave Elisa from the clutches of the Order, even if it means \ndestroying it.\nSpecial Agenda (Morgana of the Lake): We learned \nthat everything that happened to us is the fault of Morgana \nthe Witch, so we want to kidnap and force her to save Elisa \nwith her magic.\nNote: Morgana of the Lake is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"cb4TvkzaIZXD2yax","name":"The Silent","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"0HqbyCBUbSkCMC0H","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Silent","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an unscrupulous killer, I hate humanity \nand the body to which I am condemned. My voice is reduced \nto a faint whisper, which weakened my Siren powers but did \nnot take them away.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 52","positive":"I am an unscrupulous killer, I hate humanity \nand the body to which I am condemned. My voice is reduced \nto a faint whisper, which weakened my Siren powers but did \nnot take them away.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Silent","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qE5LHvHHD6ioQStu","name":"Gift - The Siren’s Whisper","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Silent","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Silent has given away \nher voice, but she can still whisper. Any opponent acting \nagainst the Silent must pass a Defense Check before taking \ntheir action, or be dazed and miss the opportunity to act. \nA target cannot be affected by this Gift more than once per \nScene.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 52","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Silent","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"EKGWBkKAEHCIgvp1","name":"Gift - The Siren’s Charm","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Silent","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Silent possesses an \notherworldly beauty that can awaken the lustful desire \nof those around her. Once per Scene, if the Silent wants, \nevery subject in her presence will receive the Descriptor: \nI desire the Silent with all my heart and would do anything \nto have her. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to resist. \nParticularly powerful NPCs, at the discretion of the \nStoryteller, may not succumb to the Siren’s Charm.\n53</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 52","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Silent","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Eaj2FVtgCVJP3gTf","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Silent","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Silent\nInspired by The Little Mermaid (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a young Mermaid who was \ncaptured by a fisherman. Sensing her worth, the greedy \nfisherman gave the Mermaid as a tribute to the local \nnobleman. He displayed her as an exotic animal, fascinating \neveryone, but particularly the nobleman’s son. Over time, the \nyoung man began to look at the Mermaid with different eyes, \nand his curiosity turned into passion. The two consummated \na forbidden desire, which led the young Mermaid to feel \nsincere love for her prince. The feeling was, unfortunately, not \nreciprocated. As soon as the opportunity arose, the nobleman’s \nson left the family home to get married. The Mermaid was \nsold to a circus, destined to end her days as a sideshow \nmonster frightening fools with her misery. The meeting with \na mysterious witch named Marina changed her destiny. In \nexchange for her voice, she obtained a shapeshifting potion. \n“Be careful, ” said the witch. “Do you really wish to give up \nwhat you are to pursue a fleeting love?” The Mermaid didn’t \nthink twice about it and drank the potion to become fully \nhuman. She returned to her prince only to find that he barely \nremembered her and their time together. The Mermaid’s \nheart darkened. On a full moon night, she drank the blood of \nher lost love, and with it that of his entire new family.\nDescriptor: I am an unscrupulous killer, I hate humanity \nand the body to which I am condemned. My voice is reduced \nto a faint whisper, which weakened my Siren powers but did \nnot take them away.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\n52\nAgenda: I work for anyone who can afford to pay with \nmagic and arcane items, which I intend to use to become a \nMermaid again.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I hate \nMarina for what she did to me. Even though she warned me \nabout what would happen, her power can ruin people’s lives. \nI want her to make me a Mermaid again before I kill her.\nGift - The Siren’s Whisper: The Silent has given away \nher voice, but she can still whisper. Any opponent acting \nagainst the Silent must pass a Defense Check before taking \ntheir action, or be dazed and miss the opportunity to act. \nA target cannot be affected by this Gift more than once per \nScene.\nGift - The Siren’s Charm: The Silent possesses an \notherworldly beauty that can awaken the lustful desire \nof those around her. Once per Scene, if the Silent wants, \nevery subject in her presence will receive the Descriptor: \nI desire the Silent with all my heart and would do anything \nto have her. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to resist. \nParticularly powerful NPCs, at the discretion of the \nStoryteller, may not succumb to the Siren’s Charm.\n53</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 52","owner":"The Silent","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-silent-52","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":52}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Silent\nInspired by The Little Mermaid (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a young Mermaid who was \ncaptured by a fisherman. Sensing her worth, the greedy \nfisherman gave the Mermaid as a tribute to the local \nnobleman. He displayed her as an exotic animal, fascinating \neveryone, but particularly the nobleman’s son. Over time, the \nyoung man began to look at the Mermaid with different eyes, \nand his curiosity turned into passion. The two consummated \na forbidden desire, which led the young Mermaid to feel \nsincere love for her prince. The feeling was, unfortunately, not \nreciprocated. As soon as the opportunity arose, the nobleman’s \nson left the family home to get married. The Mermaid was \nsold to a circus, destined to end her days as a sideshow \nmonster frightening fools with her misery. The meeting with \na mysterious witch named Marina changed her destiny. In \nexchange for her voice, she obtained a shapeshifting potion. \n“Be careful, ” said the witch. “Do you really wish to give up \nwhat you are to pursue a fleeting love?” The Mermaid didn’t \nthink twice about it and drank the potion to become fully \nhuman. She returned to her prince only to find that he barely \nremembered her and their time together. The Mermaid’s \nheart darkened. On a full moon night, she drank the blood of \nher lost love, and with it that of his entire new family.\nDescriptor: I am an unscrupulous killer, I hate humanity \nand the body to which I am condemned. My voice is reduced \nto a faint whisper, which weakened my Siren powers but did \nnot take them away.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\n52\nAgenda: I work for anyone who can afford to pay with \nmagic and arcane items, which I intend to use to become a \nMermaid again.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I hate \nMarina for what she did to me. Even though she warned me \nabout what would happen, her power can ruin people’s lives. \nI want her to make me a Mermaid again before I kill her.\nGift - The Siren’s Whisper: The Silent has given away \nher voice, but she can still whisper. Any opponent acting \nagainst the Silent must pass a Defense Check before taking \ntheir action, or be dazed and miss the opportunity to act. \nA target cannot be affected by this Gift more than once per \nScene.\nGift - The Siren’s Charm: The Silent possesses an \notherworldly beauty that can awaken the lustful desire \nof those around her. Once per Scene, if the Silent wants, \nevery subject in her presence will receive the Descriptor: \nI desire the Silent with all my heart and would do anything \nto have her. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to resist. \nParticularly powerful NPCs, at the discretion of the \nStoryteller, may not succumb to the Siren’s Charm.\n53</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I work for anyone who can afford to pay with \nmagic and arcane items, which I intend to use to become a \nMermaid again.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I hate \nMarina for what she did to me. Even though she warned me \nabout what would happen, her power can ruin people’s lives. \nI want her to make me a Mermaid again before I kill her.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Jdmtb6fMtMLCg5VI","name":"The Wise Fox","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"Qlhz77gpikIFCHBS","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Wise Fox","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an immortal spirit \nincarnated in the body of a talking fox \nand I have always watched over human \naffairs.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 54","positive":"I am an immortal spirit \nincarnated in the body of a talking fox \nand I have always watched over human \naffairs.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Wise Fox","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PXKPpn3RKCgqzAQ4","name":"Gift - A Good Advice","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Wise Fox","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per \nScene, the Wise Fox can appear to \nsomeone who has done a good deed, to \nbring advice, an object, or information that will be decisive \nfor the current Scene. Before dispensing his help, however, \nthe Fox will ask for a price to be paid. Select between: 1. \nSpilled Blood: Whoever benefits from the advice must \nself-inflict 1 Wound by shedding blood as a symbol of \ncommitment. 2. Good Action: Whoever wants to receive \nthe Fox’s help will first have to perform the requested \naction. This action, although apparently absurd, can \nbe contextualized by the Storyteller in a future \nScenario faced by the Hunters. The effort \nrequired must include difficult or dangerous \nsituations to overcome. 3. Demonstrate \nCommitment: To receive the benefit of the \nadvice, a Hunter has to go through an entire \nScene without using Gifts.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 54","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Wise Fox","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jO32FzgSrFKgCIdW","name":"Gift - Offer Help","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Wise Fox","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, the \nWise Fox can appear and help one \nwho previously paid the cost he \nrequired. A Hunter may spend 1 \nSoma to get advice from the Wise \nFox, thus receiving 2 Additional \nSuccesses on a Position Check.\n54</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 54","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Wise Fox","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"hzPBktFW0R2vms9N","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Wise Fox","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Wise Fox\nInspired by The Golden Bird (Ally)\nSince time immemorial some have set aside the wise words \nthat advised hard work and responsibility, preferring fast \nand easy rewards. When the lessons of the wise are \nignored, pain is the teacher of last resort, bringing \nwith it the awareness that every mistake has a price. \nA benevolent and kind Spirit knew this well and \nfor centuries had tried to teach mortals in order \nto spare them the pain of a harsher lesson, only \nto see them inevitably choose the less sensible \npath. Eventually, the Spirit decided to help those \nin need, but only if they could meet his price. \nIn this way, he thought, his help would be \nmore appreciated by humans, who value \nsomething more the more it costs them.\nDescriptor: I am an immortal spirit \nincarnated in the body of a talking fox \nand I have always watched over human \naffairs.\n6 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Hard 7\nAgenda: To help the humans I deem \ndeserving while asking a fair price in \nexchange.\nGift - A Good Advice: Once per \nScene, the Wise Fox can appear to \nsomeone who has done a good deed, to \nbring advice, an object, or information that will be decisive \nfor the current Scene. Before dispensing his help, however, \nthe Fox will ask for a price to be paid. Select between: 1. \nSpilled Blood: Whoever benefits from the advice must \nself-inflict 1 Wound by shedding blood as a symbol of \ncommitment. 2. Good Action: Whoever wants to receive \nthe Fox’s help will first have to perform the requested \naction. This action, although apparently absurd, can \nbe contextualized by the Storyteller in a future \nScenario faced by the Hunters. The effort \nrequired must include difficult or dangerous \nsituations to overcome. 3. Demonstrate \nCommitment: To receive the benefit of the \nadvice, a Hunter has to go through an entire \nScene without using Gifts.\nGift - Offer Help: Once per Scene, the \nWise Fox can appear and help one \nwho previously paid the cost he \nrequired. A Hunter may spend 1 \nSoma to get advice from the Wise \nFox, thus receiving 2 Additional \nSuccesses on a Position Check.\n54</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 54","owner":"The Wise Fox","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-wise-fox-54","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":54}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Wise Fox\nInspired by The Golden Bird (Ally)\nSince time immemorial some have set aside the wise words \nthat advised hard work and responsibility, preferring fast \nand easy rewards. When the lessons of the wise are \nignored, pain is the teacher of last resort, bringing \nwith it the awareness that every mistake has a price. \nA benevolent and kind Spirit knew this well and \nfor centuries had tried to teach mortals in order \nto spare them the pain of a harsher lesson, only \nto see them inevitably choose the less sensible \npath. Eventually, the Spirit decided to help those \nin need, but only if they could meet his price. \nIn this way, he thought, his help would be \nmore appreciated by humans, who value \nsomething more the more it costs them.\nDescriptor: I am an immortal spirit \nincarnated in the body of a talking fox \nand I have always watched over human \naffairs.\n6 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Hard 7\nAgenda: To help the humans I deem \ndeserving while asking a fair price in \nexchange.\nGift - A Good Advice: Once per \nScene, the Wise Fox can appear to \nsomeone who has done a good deed, to \nbring advice, an object, or information that will be decisive \nfor the current Scene. Before dispensing his help, however, \nthe Fox will ask for a price to be paid. Select between: 1. \nSpilled Blood: Whoever benefits from the advice must \nself-inflict 1 Wound by shedding blood as a symbol of \ncommitment. 2. Good Action: Whoever wants to receive \nthe Fox’s help will first have to perform the requested \naction. This action, although apparently absurd, can \nbe contextualized by the Storyteller in a future \nScenario faced by the Hunters. The effort \nrequired must include difficult or dangerous \nsituations to overcome. 3. Demonstrate \nCommitment: To receive the benefit of the \nadvice, a Hunter has to go through an entire \nScene without using Gifts.\nGift - Offer Help: Once per Scene, the \nWise Fox can appear and help one \nwho previously paid the cost he \nrequired. A Hunter may spend 1 \nSoma to get advice from the Wise \nFox, thus receiving 2 Additional \nSuccesses on a Position Check.\n54</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"To help the humans I deem \ndeserving while asking a fair price in \nexchange.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gsyPUfJH54owexf7","name":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"CWKsr978zFqCzQCB","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled alchemist and puppet master. \nHidden within my clothes are all kinds of tools and weapons, \neach useful for disassembling and reassembling bodies, whether \nof flesh or wood.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 55","positive":"I am a skilled alchemist and puppet master. \nHidden within my clothes are all kinds of tools and weapons, \neach useful for disassembling and reassembling bodies, whether \nof flesh or wood.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"c4pWyB9iMrW7g3A1","name":"Gift - The Puppets’ Rite","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Fire Eater can animate a \nPuppet by harnessing the soul of a dying person within \nit. From that moment on, the Puppet will be linked to \nits creator until he decides to free it. A Puppet has the \nfollowing profile:</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 55","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tJ2yPq1TyGiDLqSp","name":"Gift - Puppet","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>At zero Wounds a Puppet will shatter, \nbut if repaired it will immediately recover its Wound and \nreturn to action. The Descriptor of each Puppet must \nbe completed with a feature related to what they were in \nlife. Acting on that part of the Descriptor can awaken the \ndormant consciousness of the harnessed soul, allowing the \nPuppet to act independently of its master.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 55","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9SQRoo9zLmHbrIaS","name":"Gift - Master of Puppets","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Fire Eater is always \nsurrounded by at least 6 Puppets. In his presence, increase \neach Puppet’s Opposition Level by 1. When he would suffer</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 55","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CrxejGS8aFntAtyn","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Fire Eater the Puppeteer\nInspired by Pinocchio (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a skilled puppeteer obsessed with \nthe idea of creating the perfect puppet. “If only my puppets \nlooked like real humans, ” he said. “Then my puppet shows could \nreally reach people’s hearts. ” After years of study, Fire Eater \nfound an ancient alchemy book containing a bloody ritual \ncapable of binding a person’s soul to an artificial body. From \nthat day on, the puppets in Fire Eater’s traveling coach were \nnever the same... Each puppet became the receptacle of a lost \nsoul, added to the puppeteer’s grim collection.\nDescriptor: I am a skilled alchemist and puppet master. \nHidden within my clothes are all kinds of tools and weapons, \neach useful for disassembling and reassembling bodies, whether \nof flesh or wood.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Listening intently to the personal stories of those I \nmeet and judging who deserves to join my puppet collection \n/ Treating everyone equally, innocents and murderers alike, \nbecause life as a puppet is a blessing.\nSpecial Agenda (Carlo the Living Puppet): I’m always \nlooking for the perfect puppet. Once I find it, I will make it \nmine, no matter the cost.\nNote: Carlo the Living Puppet is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\n55\nGift - The Puppets’ Rite: Fire Eater can animate a \nPuppet by harnessing the soul of a dying person within \nit. From that moment on, the Puppet will be linked to \nits creator until he decides to free it. A Puppet has the \nfollowing profile:\nDescriptor: I’m an animated puppet and I do \neverything my creator says... [see the Puppet Gift below]\n1 Wound \nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nGift - Puppet: At zero Wounds a Puppet will shatter, \nbut if repaired it will immediately recover its Wound and \nreturn to action. The Descriptor of each Puppet must \nbe completed with a feature related to what they were in \nlife. Acting on that part of the Descriptor can awaken the \ndormant consciousness of the harnessed soul, allowing the \nPuppet to act independently of its master.\nGift - Master of Puppets: Fire Eater is always \nsurrounded by at least 6 Puppets. In his presence, increase \neach Puppet’s Opposition Level by 1. When he would suffer \n1 Wound, Fire Eater can sacrifice a Puppet instead.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 55","owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-fire-eater-the-puppeteer-55","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":55}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Fire Eater the Puppeteer\nInspired by Pinocchio (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a skilled puppeteer obsessed with \nthe idea of creating the perfect puppet. “If only my puppets \nlooked like real humans, ” he said. “Then my puppet shows could \nreally reach people’s hearts. ” After years of study, Fire Eater \nfound an ancient alchemy book containing a bloody ritual \ncapable of binding a person’s soul to an artificial body. From \nthat day on, the puppets in Fire Eater’s traveling coach were \nnever the same... Each puppet became the receptacle of a lost \nsoul, added to the puppeteer’s grim collection.\nDescriptor: I am a skilled alchemist and puppet master. \nHidden within my clothes are all kinds of tools and weapons, \neach useful for disassembling and reassembling bodies, whether \nof flesh or wood.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Listening intently to the personal stories of those I \nmeet and judging who deserves to join my puppet collection \n/ Treating everyone equally, innocents and murderers alike, \nbecause life as a puppet is a blessing.\nSpecial Agenda (Carlo the Living Puppet): I’m always \nlooking for the perfect puppet. Once I find it, I will make it \nmine, no matter the cost.\nNote: Carlo the Living Puppet is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\n55\nGift - The Puppets’ Rite: Fire Eater can animate a \nPuppet by harnessing the soul of a dying person within \nit. From that moment on, the Puppet will be linked to \nits creator until he decides to free it. A Puppet has the \nfollowing profile:\nDescriptor: I’m an animated puppet and I do \neverything my creator says... [see the Puppet Gift below]\n1 Wound \nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nGift - Puppet: At zero Wounds a Puppet will shatter, \nbut if repaired it will immediately recover its Wound and \nreturn to action. The Descriptor of each Puppet must \nbe completed with a feature related to what they were in \nlife. Acting on that part of the Descriptor can awaken the \ndormant consciousness of the harnessed soul, allowing the \nPuppet to act independently of its master.\nGift - Master of Puppets: Fire Eater is always \nsurrounded by at least 6 Puppets. In his presence, increase \neach Puppet’s Opposition Level by 1. When he would suffer \n1 Wound, Fire Eater can sacrifice a Puppet instead.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Listening intently to the personal stories of those I \nmeet and judging who deserves to join my puppet collection \n/ Treating everyone equally, innocents and murderers alike, \nbecause life as a puppet is a blessing.\nSpecial Agenda (Carlo the Living Puppet): I’m always \nlooking for the perfect puppet. Once I find it, I will make it \nmine, no matter the cost.\nNote: Carlo the Living Puppet is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\n55","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804721,"modifiedTime":1781556804721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MwdJ4MQHq1FCTgXB","name":"The Masked Swashbuckler","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"iLGCx1TvdpHQ2WAs","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a cunning cat who can pretend to be \nhuman thanks to a magical mask. I put myself at the service \nof the highest bidder without qualms and I use my countless \nlives to get the better of every problem.\n56</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 56","positive":"I am a cunning cat who can pretend to be \nhuman thanks to a magical mask. I put myself at the service \nof the highest bidder without qualms and I use my countless \nlives to get the better of every problem.\n56","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mVXpanlidCNMOWWd","name":"Gift - Nine Lives Like a Cat","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Masked Swashbuckler \nstill has eight lives left, so he can return to action once \nhe is taken out. When he is eliminated, the Storyteller \ncan make him disappear from the current Scene in \na blatant way or by revealing his death, even if the \nHunters just wanted him disabled. In the following \nScene, The Masked Swashbuckler will rejoin the action \nwith the following perks: 1. Once per Scene, he can \nprevent an enemy from using a Gift he has already \nseen in action previously. This effect interrupts the \ntarget and their action is wasted. 2. His Opposition \nLevel is increased by 1 when defending against an \nenemy he has already faced in a duel. 3. Once per \nScene, he can take advantage of a magical item that \nhe has previously procured to defeat his enemy. \nThe item is disposable and the Storyteller must \ncreate a Descriptor to accompany it, such as The \nInvisibility Potion or The Stone of Blinding Light.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 56","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZqL1ECTyIRyZZD4O","name":"Gift - Cat Mask","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to his magical \nmask, the Masked Swashbuckler can freely \ntransform between human and cat, taking \nadvantage of this to approach his enemy. \nThe transformation is instantaneous, but it \ncannot be done in front of witnesses.\n57</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 56","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JYwEt3YndsjkINXt","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Masked\nSwashbuckler\nInspired by the Puss in Boots (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a cunning Cat who made his \nyoung master’s fortune. But alas, as often happens, instead \nof thanking him the now rich scion was quick to abandon his \nfaithful companion. Disappointed, the Cat put himself at the \nservice of three other masters, but once success and wealth \nwere achieved, they all got rid of him. Thus it was that the \nCat swore to work only for himself. In the adventures that \nfollowed, the Cat released an ancient spirit from which he \nobtained a wish. Having heard of this miracle, the original \nungrateful master showed up, pitiful now after developing \na rare disease. He begged for forgiveness, repenting of his \narrogance, and asked the Cat to wish for a cure. In return, he \npromised eternal gratitude. The Cat accepted and made the \nwish. But, as soon as the miracle was performed the Cat’s old \nmaster killed him, fearful of his incredible abilities. \nBut even a fool knows that cats have nine lives, though his \nmaster might have forgotten. The next day the Cat returned \nfrom the dead. Enraged by the betrayal, the Cat swore \nrevenge. He put on a mask capable of making him appear \nhuman, allowing him to masquerade as a noble duelist. He \nbegan to travel to courts and drawing rooms, taking revenge \non his ungrateful masters. After killing them one by one, the \nCat developed a taste for blood and decided that from that \nday on, his only master would be money.\nDescriptor: I am a cunning cat who can pretend to be \nhuman thanks to a magical mask. I put myself at the service \nof the highest bidder without qualms and I use my countless \nlives to get the better of every problem.\n56\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: To serve my customer without asking questions / \nMocking those who trust others too much.\nGift - Nine Lives Like a Cat: The Masked Swashbuckler \nstill has eight lives left, so he can return to action once \nhe is taken out. When he is eliminated, the Storyteller \ncan make him disappear from the current Scene in \na blatant way or by revealing his death, even if the \nHunters just wanted him disabled. In the following \nScene, The Masked Swashbuckler will rejoin the action \nwith the following perks: 1. Once per Scene, he can \nprevent an enemy from using a Gift he has already \nseen in action previously. This effect interrupts the \ntarget and their action is wasted. 2. His Opposition \nLevel is increased by 1 when defending against an \nenemy he has already faced in a duel. 3. Once per \nScene, he can take advantage of a magical item that \nhe has previously procured to defeat his enemy. \nThe item is disposable and the Storyteller must \ncreate a Descriptor to accompany it, such as The \nInvisibility Potion or The Stone of Blinding Light.\nGift - Cat Mask: Thanks to his magical \nmask, the Masked Swashbuckler can freely \ntransform between human and cat, taking \nadvantage of this to approach his enemy. \nThe transformation is instantaneous, but it \ncannot be done in front of witnesses.\n57</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 56","owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-masked-swashbuckler-56","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":56}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Masked\nSwashbuckler\nInspired by the Puss in Boots (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a cunning Cat who made his \nyoung master’s fortune. But alas, as often happens, instead \nof thanking him the now rich scion was quick to abandon his \nfaithful companion. Disappointed, the Cat put himself at the \nservice of three other masters, but once success and wealth \nwere achieved, they all got rid of him. Thus it was that the \nCat swore to work only for himself. In the adventures that \nfollowed, the Cat released an ancient spirit from which he \nobtained a wish. Having heard of this miracle, the original \nungrateful master showed up, pitiful now after developing \na rare disease. He begged for forgiveness, repenting of his \narrogance, and asked the Cat to wish for a cure. In return, he \npromised eternal gratitude. The Cat accepted and made the \nwish. But, as soon as the miracle was performed the Cat’s old \nmaster killed him, fearful of his incredible abilities. \nBut even a fool knows that cats have nine lives, though his \nmaster might have forgotten. The next day the Cat returned \nfrom the dead. Enraged by the betrayal, the Cat swore \nrevenge. He put on a mask capable of making him appear \nhuman, allowing him to masquerade as a noble duelist. He \nbegan to travel to courts and drawing rooms, taking revenge \non his ungrateful masters. After killing them one by one, the \nCat developed a taste for blood and decided that from that \nday on, his only master would be money.\nDescriptor: I am a cunning cat who can pretend to be \nhuman thanks to a magical mask. I put myself at the service \nof the highest bidder without qualms and I use my countless \nlives to get the better of every problem.\n56\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: To serve my customer without asking questions / \nMocking those who trust others too much.\nGift - Nine Lives Like a Cat: The Masked Swashbuckler \nstill has eight lives left, so he can return to action once \nhe is taken out. When he is eliminated, the Storyteller \ncan make him disappear from the current Scene in \na blatant way or by revealing his death, even if the \nHunters just wanted him disabled. In the following \nScene, The Masked Swashbuckler will rejoin the action \nwith the following perks: 1. Once per Scene, he can \nprevent an enemy from using a Gift he has already \nseen in action previously. This effect interrupts the \ntarget and their action is wasted. 2. His Opposition \nLevel is increased by 1 when defending against an \nenemy he has already faced in a duel. 3. Once per \nScene, he can take advantage of a magical item that \nhe has previously procured to defeat his enemy. \nThe item is disposable and the Storyteller must \ncreate a Descriptor to accompany it, such as The \nInvisibility Potion or The Stone of Blinding Light.\nGift - Cat Mask: Thanks to his magical \nmask, the Masked Swashbuckler can freely \ntransform between human and cat, taking \nadvantage of this to approach his enemy. \nThe transformation is instantaneous, but it \ncannot be done in front of witnesses.\n57</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To serve my customer without asking questions / \nMocking those who trust others too much.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XIRkynY2RtV0SW8x","name":"Orcus the Guardian","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"IkkFHX7xkxWfc5Yp","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Orcus the Guardian","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a giant of incredible strength and repulsive \nappearance. I serve the Order as the Hunters’ Guardian and \nexecute every order to the best of my ability.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 58","positive":"I am a giant of incredible strength and repulsive \nappearance. I serve the Order as the Hunters’ Guardian and \nexecute every order to the best of my ability.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Orcus the Guardian","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"V8Ubl90AaOceHDUb","name":"Gift - Strength of the Ogre","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Orcus the Guardian","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, a Hunter can invoke Orcus’s help and use one of \nthe following effects: 1. Orcus can \nlift, move, or break either an \nobject or part of the environment, with a force equal to \nthat of five men. 2. If Orcus\n58\ncan use his strength to support another Hunter’s action, the \nHunter he aids will receive 2 Additional Successes. When \nthis Gift is used, roll a die: with a 5 or 6, Orcus unintentionally causes irreparable damage to an object, the environment, or a person while using the Gift.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 58","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Orcus the Guardian","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wpSd33YZ5IEoY586","name":"Gift - Guardian of the Hunters","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Orcus the Guardian","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, a \nHunter can invoke the protection of Orcus, who will take</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 58","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Orcus the Guardian","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1quKnT1xm5qTNdR1","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Orcus the Guardian","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Orcus the Guardian\nInspired by the Evil Orc (Ally)\nOnce upon a time, there was a gigantic and deformed man \nno one wanted to befriend. Orcus was mocked and excluded \nfrom society, until one day he met a gentle nobleman who \nknew how to look beyond his repugnant aspect. The nobleman \nmade Orcus his personal bodyguard. One day, during a trip \nto the nearby capital, the nobleman’s carriage was attacked \nby assassins. Orcus defended the nobleman and his family \nwith all his might. Lost in the heat of battle, he seized the \ncarriage itself to use as a weapon. He used it to crush his \nenemies and, unwittingly, killed all the passengers too. Orcus \nwas destroyed by grief, and the Judge who oversaw the trial \nthat followed showed him mercy. He would serve \nhis sentence as a guard for the Judge. \nBut the tragedy only repeated \nitself. During a hunt, \nthe unwary Judge \nslipped off \na cliff and was saved by the providential intervention of \nOrcus who, with his immense strength, threw the man and \nhis horse back onto the road. The impact, however, was fatal. \nThe Judge ended up smashed like a ripe apple. From job to \njob, Orcus was always welcomed by someone attracted by his \nabilities, who ultimately ended up dying in some absurd way. \nA wealthy merchant was pushed away to avoid being hit by \na cart but ended up mangled in the machinery of a nearby \nfactory... A skilled medic who fell into a river was rescued \nby Orcus, but when the hapless giant attempted to apply the \nresuscitation technique his master had taught him, the poor \nman’s rib cage cracked before exploding to pieces under the \npressure. After going from master to master, Orcus eventually \nfound a home in the Order, perhaps the only place where his \nHerculean strength could safely be put to good use.\nDescriptor: I am a giant of incredible strength and repulsive \nappearance. I serve the Order as the Hunters’ Guardian and \nexecute every order to the best of my ability.\n3 Wounds\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Do my best to serve the Hunters, but avoid killing anyone with my \nstrength.\nGift - Strength of the Ogre: \nOnce per Scene, a Hunter can invoke Orcus’s help and use one of \nthe following effects: 1. Orcus can \nlift, move, or break either an \nobject or part of the environment, with a force equal to \nthat of five men. 2. If Orcus\n58\ncan use his strength to support another Hunter’s action, the \nHunter he aids will receive 2 Additional Successes. When \nthis Gift is used, roll a die: with a 5 or 6, Orcus unintentionally causes irreparable damage to an object, the environment, or a person while using the Gift.\nGift - Guardian of the Hunters: Once per Scene, a \nHunter can invoke the protection of Orcus, who will take \n1 Wound in his place. When you use this Gift, roll a die: \non a 6, Orcus takes the Wound but inflicts 1 Wound on \nthe Hunter by accidentally overwhelming them with his \nincredible strength.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 58","owner":"Orcus the Guardian","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-orcus-the-guardian-58","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":58}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Orcus the Guardian\nInspired by the Evil Orc (Ally)\nOnce upon a time, there was a gigantic and deformed man \nno one wanted to befriend. Orcus was mocked and excluded \nfrom society, until one day he met a gentle nobleman who \nknew how to look beyond his repugnant aspect. The nobleman \nmade Orcus his personal bodyguard. One day, during a trip \nto the nearby capital, the nobleman’s carriage was attacked \nby assassins. Orcus defended the nobleman and his family \nwith all his might. Lost in the heat of battle, he seized the \ncarriage itself to use as a weapon. He used it to crush his \nenemies and, unwittingly, killed all the passengers too. Orcus \nwas destroyed by grief, and the Judge who oversaw the trial \nthat followed showed him mercy. He would serve \nhis sentence as a guard for the Judge. \nBut the tragedy only repeated \nitself. During a hunt, \nthe unwary Judge \nslipped off \na cliff and was saved by the providential intervention of \nOrcus who, with his immense strength, threw the man and \nhis horse back onto the road. The impact, however, was fatal. \nThe Judge ended up smashed like a ripe apple. From job to \njob, Orcus was always welcomed by someone attracted by his \nabilities, who ultimately ended up dying in some absurd way. \nA wealthy merchant was pushed away to avoid being hit by \na cart but ended up mangled in the machinery of a nearby \nfactory... A skilled medic who fell into a river was rescued \nby Orcus, but when the hapless giant attempted to apply the \nresuscitation technique his master had taught him, the poor \nman’s rib cage cracked before exploding to pieces under the \npressure. After going from master to master, Orcus eventually \nfound a home in the Order, perhaps the only place where his \nHerculean strength could safely be put to good use.\nDescriptor: I am a giant of incredible strength and repulsive \nappearance. I serve the Order as the Hunters’ Guardian and \nexecute every order to the best of my ability.\n3 Wounds\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Do my best to serve the Hunters, but avoid killing anyone with my \nstrength.\nGift - Strength of the Ogre: \nOnce per Scene, a Hunter can invoke Orcus’s help and use one of \nthe following effects: 1. Orcus can \nlift, move, or break either an \nobject or part of the environment, with a force equal to \nthat of five men. 2. If Orcus\n58\ncan use his strength to support another Hunter’s action, the \nHunter he aids will receive 2 Additional Successes. When \nthis Gift is used, roll a die: with a 5 or 6, Orcus unintentionally causes irreparable damage to an object, the environment, or a person while using the Gift.\nGift - Guardian of the Hunters: Once per Scene, a \nHunter can invoke the protection of Orcus, who will take \n1 Wound in his place. When you use this Gift, roll a die: \non a 6, Orcus takes the Wound but inflicts 1 Wound on \nthe Hunter by accidentally overwhelming them with his \nincredible strength.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Do my best to serve the Hunters, but avoid killing anyone with my \nstrength.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"p52m2Jkulgpg6bY2","name":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"MfcZCdIATJdzwJD3","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young mercenary who combines fighting \nskills with uncontrolled fury. My loyal war bears are my family \nand no one can lay a finger on me.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 59","positive":"I am a young mercenary who combines fighting \nskills with uncontrolled fury. My loyal war bears are my family \nand no one can lay a finger on me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"G4fPWp3XumvUh310","name":"Gift - War Bears","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Goldilocks is always accompanied by \nher three trusty War Bears. The Bears only obey her and it \nis not possible to influence their behavior or scare them, not \neven with magic. When Goldilocks acts, she can expend one \nof her Bears’ actions to obtain a single special effect: 1. Inflict \n1 additional Wound with a successful attack. 2. Cancel 1 \nWound suffered, which a Bear will take instead. 3. Increase \nthe Opposition Level of an action by 1.\nThe Three Bears</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 59","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vyThQFV1Yi1dzf5w","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>•\nGoldilocks and her \nWar Bears\nInspired by Goldilock and the Three Bears \n(Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a young orphan who, to escape \nthe clutches of a gang of thieves, took refuge in a forest. After \nwandering for days, the young woman found a bear’s den \nand, seized by desperation and hunger, ate the honey she \nfound there. Exhausted and cold, she recklessly fell asleep in \nthe den. When the bear came home it pounced on her, but the \ngirl managed to defend herself with an old knife found stuck \nin the bones of a careless hunter. The young woman got the \nbetter of the feral animal and slit its throat. Before dying the \nbear inflicted dozens of deep wounds that spoiled her good \nlooks forever. Desperate but determined to survive, Goldilocks \nheard a moan coming from the bottom of the den. She found \nthree newborn bears, orphans of the mother she just killed. \nShe took the cubs with her and, from that day, promised that \nno one would ever toy with her life again. Years later, a rumor \nwas heard often across the battlefields, of Goldilocks and her \nwar bears who were revered and feared as the most dangerous \nof all mercenaries.\n59\nDescriptor: I am a young mercenary who combines fighting \nskills with uncontrolled fury. My loyal war bears are my family \nand no one can lay a finger on me.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5 \nAgenda: Live without anyone telling me what I should or can \ndo / Take care of my beautiful blonde hair, the only part of my \nbody that hasn’t been spoiled.\nGift - War Bears: Goldilocks is always accompanied by \nher three trusty War Bears. The Bears only obey her and it \nis not possible to influence their behavior or scare them, not \neven with magic. When Goldilocks acts, she can expend one \nof her Bears’ actions to obtain a single special effect: 1. Inflict \n1 additional Wound with a successful attack. 2. Cancel 1 \nWound suffered, which a Bear will take instead. 3. Increase \nthe Opposition Level of an action by 1.\nThe Three Bears\nDescriptor: We are Goldilocks’ children and fight alongside \nher with unstoppable fury.\nFang - 3 Wounds Opposition Level: Easy 3 \nBlack - 1 Wound Opposition Level: Hard 7\nClaw - 2 Wound Opposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Defending our mother at any cost.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 59","owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-goldilocks-and-her-war-bears-59","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":59}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>•\nGoldilocks and her \nWar Bears\nInspired by Goldilock and the Three Bears \n(Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a young orphan who, to escape \nthe clutches of a gang of thieves, took refuge in a forest. After \nwandering for days, the young woman found a bear’s den \nand, seized by desperation and hunger, ate the honey she \nfound there. Exhausted and cold, she recklessly fell asleep in \nthe den. When the bear came home it pounced on her, but the \ngirl managed to defend herself with an old knife found stuck \nin the bones of a careless hunter. The young woman got the \nbetter of the feral animal and slit its throat. Before dying the \nbear inflicted dozens of deep wounds that spoiled her good \nlooks forever. Desperate but determined to survive, Goldilocks \nheard a moan coming from the bottom of the den. She found \nthree newborn bears, orphans of the mother she just killed. \nShe took the cubs with her and, from that day, promised that \nno one would ever toy with her life again. Years later, a rumor \nwas heard often across the battlefields, of Goldilocks and her \nwar bears who were revered and feared as the most dangerous \nof all mercenaries.\n59\nDescriptor: I am a young mercenary who combines fighting \nskills with uncontrolled fury. My loyal war bears are my family \nand no one can lay a finger on me.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5 \nAgenda: Live without anyone telling me what I should or can \ndo / Take care of my beautiful blonde hair, the only part of my \nbody that hasn’t been spoiled.\nGift - War Bears: Goldilocks is always accompanied by \nher three trusty War Bears. The Bears only obey her and it \nis not possible to influence their behavior or scare them, not \neven with magic. When Goldilocks acts, she can expend one \nof her Bears’ actions to obtain a single special effect: 1. Inflict \n1 additional Wound with a successful attack. 2. Cancel 1 \nWound suffered, which a Bear will take instead. 3. Increase \nthe Opposition Level of an action by 1.\nThe Three Bears\nDescriptor: We are Goldilocks’ children and fight alongside \nher with unstoppable fury.\nFang - 3 Wounds Opposition Level: Easy 3 \nBlack - 1 Wound Opposition Level: Hard 7\nClaw - 2 Wound Opposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Defending our mother at any cost.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Live without anyone telling me what I should or can \ndo / Take care of my beautiful blonde hair, the only part of my \nbody that hasn’t been spoiled.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9ybcYIhGgXXDrEX0","name":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"Z7sHqsozUv9LUG3z","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an experienced traveler and have seen \nevery known land. I get bored easily if I’m not interested in \nwhat I’m doing.\n1 Wound</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 60","positive":"I am an experienced traveler and have seen \nevery known land. I get bored easily if I’m not interested in \nwhat I’m doing.\n1 Wound","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Bf5udRq2dKL8gFgp","name":"Gift - Traveler of a Thousand Places","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Sinbad has seen \nthe whole world and much of what the Broken Tales hide. \nIn the course of a Scene, a Hunter can invoke his help to \nobtain information or create an additional Descriptor that \nrepresents a specific area of Sinbad’s knowledge. But the \nold sailor is an eccentric type, and to provide his help he \nfirst must be entertained. The Storyteller will evaluate the \ncurrent situation and Sinbad’s level of boredom. A Hunter \ncan capture Sinbad’s interest with creative actions, as long \nas they’re appropriate to the current Scene.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 60","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4XYoxcl40oypkLbx","name":"Gift - I Know How To Do It","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, a Hunter \ncan get 1 Additional Success in his Check, asking Sinbad \nfor helpful advice. As with Traveler of a Thousand Places, \nSinbad needs to be intrigued before helping.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 60","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tW92yIg10wcFO0b2","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Sinbad the Traveler of \na Thousand Seas\nInspired by Sinbad from One Thousand and One \nNights (Ally)\nOnce upon a time, there was a skilled sailor who traveled every \nsea and witnessed every land. Dissatisfied and bored, Sinbad \nturned to the strangest and darkest legends to find something \nthat could arouse his interest. Learning of The Broken Tales \nwas for him the discovery of a new world. From that moment \non, Sinbad became a seeker of forbidden treasures, hungry for \ndark knowledge and secrets concealed from the eyes of mere \nmortals. It was only a matter of time before he caught the attention of the Order. Sinbad willingly put himself at the service \nof the Hunters, offering his great experience in exchange for \nthe rare opportunity to feel the thrill of discovery once again.\nDescriptor: I am an experienced traveler and have seen \nevery known land. I get bored easily if I’m not interested in \nwhat I’m doing.\n1 Wound \nOpposition Level: Medium 5 \nAgenda: I am willing to do anything to experience the thrill \nof discovery once again. .\nSpecial Agenda (Sherazade, the Weaver of Tales): \nI’m boost of knowing every story and legend, and I love to \nmock those who pride themselves on limited knowledge. I \nwant to ridicule the stories Sherazade tells, highlighting the \ntruths that only I know.\nNote: Sherazade the Weaver of Tales is one of the Hunters \nfeatured in The Broken Ones expansion book.\n60\nGift - Traveler of a Thousand Places: Sinbad has seen \nthe whole world and much of what the Broken Tales hide. \nIn the course of a Scene, a Hunter can invoke his help to \nobtain information or create an additional Descriptor that \nrepresents a specific area of Sinbad’s knowledge. But the \nold sailor is an eccentric type, and to provide his help he \nfirst must be entertained. The Storyteller will evaluate the \ncurrent situation and Sinbad’s level of boredom. A Hunter \ncan capture Sinbad’s interest with creative actions, as long \nas they’re appropriate to the current Scene.\nGift - I Know How To Do It: Once per Scene, a Hunter \ncan get 1 Additional Success in his Check, asking Sinbad \nfor helpful advice. As with Traveler of a Thousand Places, \nSinbad needs to be intrigued before helping.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 60","owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas-60","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":60}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Sinbad the Traveler of \na Thousand Seas\nInspired by Sinbad from One Thousand and One \nNights (Ally)\nOnce upon a time, there was a skilled sailor who traveled every \nsea and witnessed every land. Dissatisfied and bored, Sinbad \nturned to the strangest and darkest legends to find something \nthat could arouse his interest. Learning of The Broken Tales \nwas for him the discovery of a new world. From that moment \non, Sinbad became a seeker of forbidden treasures, hungry for \ndark knowledge and secrets concealed from the eyes of mere \nmortals. It was only a matter of time before he caught the attention of the Order. Sinbad willingly put himself at the service \nof the Hunters, offering his great experience in exchange for \nthe rare opportunity to feel the thrill of discovery once again.\nDescriptor: I am an experienced traveler and have seen \nevery known land. I get bored easily if I’m not interested in \nwhat I’m doing.\n1 Wound \nOpposition Level: Medium 5 \nAgenda: I am willing to do anything to experience the thrill \nof discovery once again. .\nSpecial Agenda (Sherazade, the Weaver of Tales): \nI’m boost of knowing every story and legend, and I love to \nmock those who pride themselves on limited knowledge. I \nwant to ridicule the stories Sherazade tells, highlighting the \ntruths that only I know.\nNote: Sherazade the Weaver of Tales is one of the Hunters \nfeatured in The Broken Ones expansion book.\n60\nGift - Traveler of a Thousand Places: Sinbad has seen \nthe whole world and much of what the Broken Tales hide. \nIn the course of a Scene, a Hunter can invoke his help to \nobtain information or create an additional Descriptor that \nrepresents a specific area of Sinbad’s knowledge. But the \nold sailor is an eccentric type, and to provide his help he \nfirst must be entertained. The Storyteller will evaluate the \ncurrent situation and Sinbad’s level of boredom. A Hunter \ncan capture Sinbad’s interest with creative actions, as long \nas they’re appropriate to the current Scene.\nGift - I Know How To Do It: Once per Scene, a Hunter \ncan get 1 Additional Success in his Check, asking Sinbad \nfor helpful advice. As with Traveler of a Thousand Places, \nSinbad needs to be intrigued before helping.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am willing to do anything to experience the thrill \nof discovery once again. .\nSpecial Agenda (Sherazade, the Weaver of Tales): \nI’m boost of knowing every story and legend, and I love to \nmock those who pride themselves on limited knowledge. I \nwant to ridicule the stories Sherazade tells, highlighting the \ntruths that only I know.\nNote: Sherazade the Weaver of Tales is one of the Hunters \nfeatured in The Broken Ones expansion book.\n60","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XGvWmHYDO1mNk4wP","name":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"tU1XNWSagdkEIbD3","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a usurer of secrets, and will sell them at \na high price. If I die, I become a ghost until I am reborn in \nflesh and blood.\n61\n1 Wound</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 61","positive":"I am a usurer of secrets, and will sell them at \na high price. If I die, I become a ghost until I am reborn in \nflesh and blood.\n61\n1 Wound","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7r8iZDsWi2wwMLuS","name":"Gift - The Returning Ghost","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>When Alfred is killed he \nbecomes a ghost and, after one or more Scenes (at the Storyteller’s \ndiscretion), he will come back to life. When this happens, his \nOpposition Level goes up one rank (at first Medium 5 and then \nHard 7) and he gains 1 Wound. After being killed the third time, \nAlfred will revert to his normal profile, forgetting who killed \nhim. In ghost form, Alfred has no memories of when he was \nalive and wanders like a restless soul in the city cemetery. The \nOpposition Level remains Easy 3 and the Agenda changes.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 61","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"K67WMus6Ey9DRmPX","name":"Gift - Trader of Secrets","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>When the talking Ghost engages \nin a conversation with someone, he will compel them to share \na secret or sin they have committed. A Hunter can oppose the \neffect of this Gift with a Defense Check. The Talking Ghost \nalways knows a secret related to one or more of the NPCs linked \nto the Scenario in which he appears.\n62</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 61","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xWw7Nb9VUjVDDYtA","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>•\nAlfred Leaves the Talking \nGhost\nInspired by Pinocchio’s Jiminy Cricket\nDark Presence by the Storymancer Collective \n(Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a rich and powerful criminal \nnamed Alfred Leaves. Secrets were his weapons and his \nbusiness, and there was no one in London who did not have \nunfinished business with him. Or, more simply, had some \nunspeakably shameful secret uncovered by Leaves. He became \nmore and more obsessed with secrets, his thirst for knowledge \nextending far beyond the affairs of miserable mortals. Who \nhad created the world? What was there after death? In a \nfrenzied madness, Alfred Leaves took his life by striking \nhimself on the temple with a heavy hammer. Returning as a \nghost, Leaves encountered the One Who Plots in the Shadow. \nFinally, everything was clear to him. After a few days, Leaves \nwoke up, alive once more and ready to restart his business of \nsecrets on behalf of a new and dark master.\nDescriptor: I am a usurer of secrets, and will sell them at \na high price. If I die, I become a ghost until I am reborn in \nflesh and blood.\n61\n1 Wound\nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: When I am alive, I want to discover all the secrets I \ncan, in order to report them to the One Who Plots in the Shadow \n/ When I am dead, I walk around like a ghost and feel the need to \nshare the secrets I know. \nSpecial Agenda (Carlo the Living Puppet): I hate lying, \nbecause it does nothing but devalue a secret. That little animated \npuppet is the ultimate representation of the power of lying and I \nwant to stop him from speaking.\nNote: Carlo the Living Puppet (inspired by Pinocchio) is one of \nthe Hunters featured in The Broken Ones expansion book.\nGift - The Returning Ghost: When Alfred is killed he \nbecomes a ghost and, after one or more Scenes (at the Storyteller’s \ndiscretion), he will come back to life. When this happens, his \nOpposition Level goes up one rank (at first Medium 5 and then \nHard 7) and he gains 1 Wound. After being killed the third time, \nAlfred will revert to his normal profile, forgetting who killed \nhim. In ghost form, Alfred has no memories of when he was \nalive and wanders like a restless soul in the city cemetery. The \nOpposition Level remains Easy 3 and the Agenda changes.\n \nGift - Trader of Secrets: When the talking Ghost engages \nin a conversation with someone, he will compel them to share \na secret or sin they have committed. A Hunter can oppose the \neffect of this Gift with a Defense Check. The Talking Ghost \nalways knows a secret related to one or more of the NPCs linked \nto the Scenario in which he appears.\n62</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 61","owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost-61","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":61}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>•\nAlfred Leaves the Talking \nGhost\nInspired by Pinocchio’s Jiminy Cricket\nDark Presence by the Storymancer Collective \n(Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a rich and powerful criminal \nnamed Alfred Leaves. Secrets were his weapons and his \nbusiness, and there was no one in London who did not have \nunfinished business with him. Or, more simply, had some \nunspeakably shameful secret uncovered by Leaves. He became \nmore and more obsessed with secrets, his thirst for knowledge \nextending far beyond the affairs of miserable mortals. Who \nhad created the world? What was there after death? In a \nfrenzied madness, Alfred Leaves took his life by striking \nhimself on the temple with a heavy hammer. Returning as a \nghost, Leaves encountered the One Who Plots in the Shadow. \nFinally, everything was clear to him. After a few days, Leaves \nwoke up, alive once more and ready to restart his business of \nsecrets on behalf of a new and dark master.\nDescriptor: I am a usurer of secrets, and will sell them at \na high price. If I die, I become a ghost until I am reborn in \nflesh and blood.\n61\n1 Wound\nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: When I am alive, I want to discover all the secrets I \ncan, in order to report them to the One Who Plots in the Shadow \n/ When I am dead, I walk around like a ghost and feel the need to \nshare the secrets I know. \nSpecial Agenda (Carlo the Living Puppet): I hate lying, \nbecause it does nothing but devalue a secret. That little animated \npuppet is the ultimate representation of the power of lying and I \nwant to stop him from speaking.\nNote: Carlo the Living Puppet (inspired by Pinocchio) is one of \nthe Hunters featured in The Broken Ones expansion book.\nGift - The Returning Ghost: When Alfred is killed he \nbecomes a ghost and, after one or more Scenes (at the Storyteller’s \ndiscretion), he will come back to life. When this happens, his \nOpposition Level goes up one rank (at first Medium 5 and then \nHard 7) and he gains 1 Wound. After being killed the third time, \nAlfred will revert to his normal profile, forgetting who killed \nhim. In ghost form, Alfred has no memories of when he was \nalive and wanders like a restless soul in the city cemetery. The \nOpposition Level remains Easy 3 and the Agenda changes.\n \nGift - Trader of Secrets: When the talking Ghost engages \nin a conversation with someone, he will compel them to share \na secret or sin they have committed. A Hunter can oppose the \neffect of this Gift with a Defense Check. The Talking Ghost \nalways knows a secret related to one or more of the NPCs linked \nto the Scenario in which he appears.\n62</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"When I am alive, I want to discover all the secrets I \ncan, in order to report them to the One Who Plots in the Shadow \n/ When I am dead, I walk around like a ghost and feel the need to \nshare the secrets I know. \nSpecial Agenda (Carlo the Living Puppet): I hate lying, \nbecause it does nothing but devalue a secret. That little animated \npuppet is the ultimate representation of the power of lying and I \nwant to stop him from speaking.\nNote: Carlo the Living Puppet (inspired by Pinocchio) is one of \nthe Hunters featured in The Broken Ones expansion book.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xd5xu1aXRraNsvoz","name":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"67wPvqyPzT9Y1SuG","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a twisted, lonely being \nwho wanders the forests and rewards \ncompanionship and kindness with \nboons.\n1 Wound</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 63","positive":"I am a twisted, lonely being \nwho wanders the forests and rewards \ncompanionship and kindness with \nboons.\n1 Wound","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"SVwrjRYajxLuaGn7","name":"Gift - Rotten Face","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Oakheart removes \nher mask, revealing her terrifying \nface. Any creature who glimpses it is \ndriven temporarily mad. The madness \ncan take the form of single-minded \nterror or gibbering catatonia. Create \na Descriptor to represent the insanity \ninduced by the vision of Oakheart’s face, \nand inflict 1 Wound on anyone who sees \nit. Alternatively, Oakheart can bestow \nits hideous face on a Hunter, who will \nreceive the ability to use this Gift once \nduring the Scenario.\n63</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 63","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wuuNtEybdChEwo2D","name":"Gift - Blossom Boon","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>After experiencing love or true \nfriendship with a person, Oakheart’s withered branches \nburst into bloom, raining petals on her and her new bond. \nThis generates 3 Petal Tokens. Each can be used to heal 1 \nWound. Alternatively, you can use 1 Petal to calm a subject \nin the grip of negative feelings, so that they can ignore \nDescriptors and Agendas related to the altered state for the \nrest of the Scene.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 63","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6f6t3XFX1VHYzAHn","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Oakheart\nthe Lady of the Woods\nInspired by Blodeuwedd (Ally)\nDark Presence by Chris \nvan der Linden and Chris \n“Mono” Mahon\nThose who venture into darkened woods \nand lonely forests whisper of a twisted \nwoman with skin made of bark, legs \nmade of coiling roots, and a face hidden \nby a crude wooden mask. Offered as the \nmortal bride to a forest god centuries \nago, the woman was transformed into a \nhideous being to please her new groom \nbut soon watched her husband wither and \ndie as the forest was cut down. Now bereft \nof her home and her love, she wanders \nthe woods in search of companionship. \nDubbed “Oakheart, ” it’s rumored that \nany mortal who glimpses her true face \nis instantly driven mad by her terrifying \ncountenance, but some wanderers claim \nto have been aided or even rescued by the \ncreature, who seems attracted to young \nand beautiful travelers.\nDescriptor: I am a twisted, lonely being \nwho wanders the forests and rewards \ncompanionship and kindness with \nboons.\n1 Wound\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Find companions willing to \nlook beyond my appearance and treat me \nwith kindness. I am attracted to those who \nare particularly beautiful, as I secretly \ndesire a lover.\n \nGift - Rotten Face: Oakheart removes \nher mask, revealing her terrifying \nface. Any creature who glimpses it is \ndriven temporarily mad. The madness \ncan take the form of single-minded \nterror or gibbering catatonia. Create \na Descriptor to represent the insanity \ninduced by the vision of Oakheart’s face, \nand inflict 1 Wound on anyone who sees \nit. Alternatively, Oakheart can bestow \nits hideous face on a Hunter, who will \nreceive the ability to use this Gift once \nduring the Scenario.\n63\nGift - Blossom Boon: After experiencing love or true \nfriendship with a person, Oakheart’s withered branches \nburst into bloom, raining petals on her and her new bond. \nThis generates 3 Petal Tokens. Each can be used to heal 1 \nWound. Alternatively, you can use 1 Petal to calm a subject \nin the grip of negative feelings, so that they can ignore \nDescriptors and Agendas related to the altered state for the \nrest of the Scene.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 63","owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods-63","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":63}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Oakheart\nthe Lady of the Woods\nInspired by Blodeuwedd (Ally)\nDark Presence by Chris \nvan der Linden and Chris \n“Mono” Mahon\nThose who venture into darkened woods \nand lonely forests whisper of a twisted \nwoman with skin made of bark, legs \nmade of coiling roots, and a face hidden \nby a crude wooden mask. Offered as the \nmortal bride to a forest god centuries \nago, the woman was transformed into a \nhideous being to please her new groom \nbut soon watched her husband wither and \ndie as the forest was cut down. Now bereft \nof her home and her love, she wanders \nthe woods in search of companionship. \nDubbed “Oakheart, ” it’s rumored that \nany mortal who glimpses her true face \nis instantly driven mad by her terrifying \ncountenance, but some wanderers claim \nto have been aided or even rescued by the \ncreature, who seems attracted to young \nand beautiful travelers.\nDescriptor: I am a twisted, lonely being \nwho wanders the forests and rewards \ncompanionship and kindness with \nboons.\n1 Wound\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Find companions willing to \nlook beyond my appearance and treat me \nwith kindness. I am attracted to those who \nare particularly beautiful, as I secretly \ndesire a lover.\n \nGift - Rotten Face: Oakheart removes \nher mask, revealing her terrifying \nface. Any creature who glimpses it is \ndriven temporarily mad. The madness \ncan take the form of single-minded \nterror or gibbering catatonia. Create \na Descriptor to represent the insanity \ninduced by the vision of Oakheart’s face, \nand inflict 1 Wound on anyone who sees \nit. Alternatively, Oakheart can bestow \nits hideous face on a Hunter, who will \nreceive the ability to use this Gift once \nduring the Scenario.\n63\nGift - Blossom Boon: After experiencing love or true \nfriendship with a person, Oakheart’s withered branches \nburst into bloom, raining petals on her and her new bond. \nThis generates 3 Petal Tokens. Each can be used to heal 1 \nWound. Alternatively, you can use 1 Petal to calm a subject \nin the grip of negative feelings, so that they can ignore \nDescriptors and Agendas related to the altered state for the \nrest of the Scene.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Find companions willing to \nlook beyond my appearance and treat me \nwith kindness. I am attracted to those who \nare particularly beautiful, as I secretly \ndesire a lover.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zZjJeV73YKFDpPeD","name":"The Feral Musicians of Bremen","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"HrucFtW11pBDvWEs","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Feral Musicians of Bremen","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a place full of violence and suffering, \nable to awaken the deepest fears in the souls of those who \napproach.\n64</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 64","positive":"I am a place full of violence and suffering, \nable to awaken the deepest fears in the souls of those who \napproach.\n64","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Feral Musicians of Bremen","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WwM9DwVNYhjpIwEg","name":"Gift - Cacophony","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Feral Musicians of Bremen","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Whether it be the words of the Judge, \nthe spells of the Witch, the barking of the Hunter’s hound, \nor the braying of the Monster, the cacophony of horrible \nnoises emitted by the entities inhabiting the Inn is more \nthan enough to make even the sturdiest soul waver. Any \naction performed inside the Inn during the manifestation \nof one of its aspects receives a 1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 64","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Feral Musicians of Bremen","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XLe1PnKO4zsylH0B","name":"Gift - A Past of Suffering","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Feral Musicians of Bremen","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>When one of the Musicians \nis hit, the suffering of the Inn’s victims overwhelms the \nattacker, causing cuts and bruises, then forcing them to \nrelive a moment in which they lost something important. \nInflicting 1 Wound to one of the Musicians requires a \nDefense Check in order not to suffer 1 Wound in turn. Once \na total of 4 Wounds is inflicted on the Musicians, they quiet \ndown for the rest of the Scene, to regenerate completely in \nthe following one. The only way to truly destroy them is to \nraze the Inn itself.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 64","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Feral Musicians of Bremen","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CAoulf1T6eMDufDu","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Feral Musicians of Bremen","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Feral Musicians \nof Bremen\nInspired by The Bremen Town Musicians \n(Neutral)\nDark Presence by Claudio Serena\nNear Bremen in the deep north of Germany, there is a small \nInn that more experienced travelers recommend avoiding, \ncalled “The Musicians”. The Inn was home for many refugees \nand slaves who were abused by their masters or fleeing their \npast. It was a safe place where the long arm of the law could \nnot find them. Over time, the Inn has also attracted bandits \nand criminals of the worst kind, eventually becoming a \nhaunted place that travelers avoid and mothers use to scare \nchildren who do not want to sleep. From the main hall, you \ncan hear a cacophony of horrible noises that no human being \ncould produce. Due to the violence that has taken place there, \nthe Inn has acquired a life of its own by making the pain \nand fear of all those who have sought refuge there its own. \nWhoever stays, by mistake or desperation, will encounter one \nof the four aspects that the Inn is able to manifest, namely the \nMusicians: the Witch, always followed by her black cat; the \nHunter, armed with a knife and accompanied by his hound; \nthe Judge, whose cock’s feather writes the faults of those who \nmeet his gaze; and the Monster, a shapeless creature whose \nbraying can lead to madness.\nDescriptor: I am a place full of violence and suffering, \nable to awaken the deepest fears in the souls of those who \napproach.\n64\n4 Wounds (1 per Musician)\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Feed the fears of the patrons, corrupting their \nminds so they will revel in the violence that follows.\nGift - Cacophony: Whether it be the words of the Judge, \nthe spells of the Witch, the barking of the Hunter’s hound, \nor the braying of the Monster, the cacophony of horrible \nnoises emitted by the entities inhabiting the Inn is more \nthan enough to make even the sturdiest soul waver. Any \naction performed inside the Inn during the manifestation \nof one of its aspects receives a 1 Penalty.\nGift - A Past of Suffering: When one of the Musicians \nis hit, the suffering of the Inn’s victims overwhelms the \nattacker, causing cuts and bruises, then forcing them to \nrelive a moment in which they lost something important. \nInflicting 1 Wound to one of the Musicians requires a \nDefense Check in order not to suffer 1 Wound in turn. Once \na total of 4 Wounds is inflicted on the Musicians, they quiet \ndown for the rest of the Scene, to regenerate completely in \nthe following one. The only way to truly destroy them is to \nraze the Inn itself.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 64","owner":"The Feral Musicians of Bremen","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-feral-musicians-of-bremen-64","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":64}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Feral Musicians \nof Bremen\nInspired by The Bremen Town Musicians \n(Neutral)\nDark Presence by Claudio Serena\nNear Bremen in the deep north of Germany, there is a small \nInn that more experienced travelers recommend avoiding, \ncalled “The Musicians”. The Inn was home for many refugees \nand slaves who were abused by their masters or fleeing their \npast. It was a safe place where the long arm of the law could \nnot find them. Over time, the Inn has also attracted bandits \nand criminals of the worst kind, eventually becoming a \nhaunted place that travelers avoid and mothers use to scare \nchildren who do not want to sleep. From the main hall, you \ncan hear a cacophony of horrible noises that no human being \ncould produce. Due to the violence that has taken place there, \nthe Inn has acquired a life of its own by making the pain \nand fear of all those who have sought refuge there its own. \nWhoever stays, by mistake or desperation, will encounter one \nof the four aspects that the Inn is able to manifest, namely the \nMusicians: the Witch, always followed by her black cat; the \nHunter, armed with a knife and accompanied by his hound; \nthe Judge, whose cock’s feather writes the faults of those who \nmeet his gaze; and the Monster, a shapeless creature whose \nbraying can lead to madness.\nDescriptor: I am a place full of violence and suffering, \nable to awaken the deepest fears in the souls of those who \napproach.\n64\n4 Wounds (1 per Musician)\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Feed the fears of the patrons, corrupting their \nminds so they will revel in the violence that follows.\nGift - Cacophony: Whether it be the words of the Judge, \nthe spells of the Witch, the barking of the Hunter’s hound, \nor the braying of the Monster, the cacophony of horrible \nnoises emitted by the entities inhabiting the Inn is more \nthan enough to make even the sturdiest soul waver. Any \naction performed inside the Inn during the manifestation \nof one of its aspects receives a 1 Penalty.\nGift - A Past of Suffering: When one of the Musicians \nis hit, the suffering of the Inn’s victims overwhelms the \nattacker, causing cuts and bruises, then forcing them to \nrelive a moment in which they lost something important. \nInflicting 1 Wound to one of the Musicians requires a \nDefense Check in order not to suffer 1 Wound in turn. Once \na total of 4 Wounds is inflicted on the Musicians, they quiet \ndown for the rest of the Scene, to regenerate completely in \nthe following one. The only way to truly destroy them is to \nraze the Inn itself.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Feed the fears of the patrons, corrupting their \nminds so they will revel in the violence that follows.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ZsYxYaJdlGNBHjpz","name":"The Returning Wolf","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"ZkRWNk8RPqRcQAe4","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Returning Wolf","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the Returning Wolf: I am bad, hungry, \nand now I am the hunter.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 65","positive":"I am the Returning Wolf: I am bad, hungry, \nand now I am the hunter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Returning Wolf","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IB8ejSRy9cqogoso","name":"Gift - Frightening Revenant","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Returning Wolf","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Wolf reveals horrific \nmutilations, each revealing something about his deaths. His \nempty eyes are as cold and bottomless as the well he was \ndrowned in. His pelt is a patchwork of burns and skinned \nflesh. His belly is full of slashes and stitches. His growl is \na terrifying sound, grinding painfully from a chest full of \nheavy stones and broken bones. No NPCs will approach \nor fight the Wolf, being paralyzed by terror. Particularly \npowerful NPCs, at the Storyteller’s discretion, can ignore \nthis effect. When a Hunter acts against the Returning Wolf, \nthey suffer 1 Penalty for each action taken.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 65","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Returning Wolf","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Afl4JUAJ6k6i2TY0","name":"Gift - The Better to Eat You With","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Returning Wolf","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Wolf can \nswallow his enemies whole, trapping them inside his belly \nand crushing them to death with the heavy stones the \ngrandmother sewed inside it. When the Returning Wolf \ninflicts 1 Wound, it can swallow the victim whole as an \nadditional effect. In the next action, the victim can only \ntry to free themselves. If they fail the Position Check, or if \nthey decide to stay in the belly of the Returning Wolf, they \nreceive 1 additional Wound.\n66</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 65","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Returning Wolf","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fDZQgorHPX5CD15N","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Returning Wolf","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>•\nThe Returning Wolf\nInspired by the Bad Wolf (Opponent)\nDark Presence by Peter Chiykowski \nIn the days when his heart still beat and his lungs still \ndrew breath, this wicked animal used to prowl the woods, \navoiding the huntsman who had long hunted him for his pelt, \nand stalking for a tasty bite amongst unsuspecting human \ntravelers. Imbued with the powers of human speech and \ncunning, the wolf tricked his victims into betraying their loved \nones into his clutches as well. He fed well until the fateful day \nhe ate up the little girl in the red hood and her grandmother. \nThat was the day the huntsman caught and slew the Wolf. \nAs the story of his death spread and changed from telling to \ntelling, he was tortured and executed in a dozen gruesome \nways: drowned in a trough, boiled in a pot, smashed into the \nground, cut down, cut open and his belly filled with heavy\n65\nstones. The many tellings bled together and the Wolf, mangled \nby countless hands and condemned by countless tongues, has \nreturned to claim revenge for every death he was subjected \nto. He is everything that has been said about him. Big. Bad \nAnd out for blood.\nDescriptor: I am the Returning Wolf: I am bad, hungry, \nand now I am the hunter.\n3 Wounds\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: I am hell-bent on revenge on the human world. I \nam a revenant animated by undying acrimony for the softskinned creatures that invaded my woods and yet had the \naudacity to condemn me to death. My only goal now is to \nglut my endless hunger for human flesh and fear. I have a \nparticular hatred for children, the elderly, and Hunters, \nwhom I see as responsible for my many deaths.\nSpecial Agenda (Iskra the Young Wolf): I harbor \na deep hatred for this little pest. She is somewhat linked to \nmy pain. I want to swallow her and let her slowly die in my \nstomach.\nNote: Iskra the Y oung Wolf is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\nSpecial Agenda (Garou the Old Wolf): I want to warn \nthe poor fool so that he understands what he will face if he \nkeeps by the side of these blasted humans. \nGift - Frightening Revenant: The Wolf reveals horrific \nmutilations, each revealing something about his deaths. His \nempty eyes are as cold and bottomless as the well he was \ndrowned in. His pelt is a patchwork of burns and skinned \nflesh. His belly is full of slashes and stitches. His growl is \na terrifying sound, grinding painfully from a chest full of \nheavy stones and broken bones. No NPCs will approach \nor fight the Wolf, being paralyzed by terror. Particularly \npowerful NPCs, at the Storyteller’s discretion, can ignore \nthis effect. When a Hunter acts against the Returning Wolf, \nthey suffer 1 Penalty for each action taken.\nGift - The Better to Eat You With: The Wolf can \nswallow his enemies whole, trapping them inside his belly \nand crushing them to death with the heavy stones the \ngrandmother sewed inside it. When the Returning Wolf \ninflicts 1 Wound, it can swallow the victim whole as an \nadditional effect. In the next action, the victim can only \ntry to free themselves. If they fail the Position Check, or if \nthey decide to stay in the belly of the Returning Wolf, they \nreceive 1 additional Wound.\n66</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 65","owner":"The Returning Wolf","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-returning-wolf-65","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":65}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>•\nThe Returning Wolf\nInspired by the Bad Wolf (Opponent)\nDark Presence by Peter Chiykowski \nIn the days when his heart still beat and his lungs still \ndrew breath, this wicked animal used to prowl the woods, \navoiding the huntsman who had long hunted him for his pelt, \nand stalking for a tasty bite amongst unsuspecting human \ntravelers. Imbued with the powers of human speech and \ncunning, the wolf tricked his victims into betraying their loved \nones into his clutches as well. He fed well until the fateful day \nhe ate up the little girl in the red hood and her grandmother. \nThat was the day the huntsman caught and slew the Wolf. \nAs the story of his death spread and changed from telling to \ntelling, he was tortured and executed in a dozen gruesome \nways: drowned in a trough, boiled in a pot, smashed into the \nground, cut down, cut open and his belly filled with heavy\n65\nstones. The many tellings bled together and the Wolf, mangled \nby countless hands and condemned by countless tongues, has \nreturned to claim revenge for every death he was subjected \nto. He is everything that has been said about him. Big. Bad \nAnd out for blood.\nDescriptor: I am the Returning Wolf: I am bad, hungry, \nand now I am the hunter.\n3 Wounds\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: I am hell-bent on revenge on the human world. I \nam a revenant animated by undying acrimony for the softskinned creatures that invaded my woods and yet had the \naudacity to condemn me to death. My only goal now is to \nglut my endless hunger for human flesh and fear. I have a \nparticular hatred for children, the elderly, and Hunters, \nwhom I see as responsible for my many deaths.\nSpecial Agenda (Iskra the Young Wolf): I harbor \na deep hatred for this little pest. She is somewhat linked to \nmy pain. I want to swallow her and let her slowly die in my \nstomach.\nNote: Iskra the Y oung Wolf is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\nSpecial Agenda (Garou the Old Wolf): I want to warn \nthe poor fool so that he understands what he will face if he \nkeeps by the side of these blasted humans. \nGift - Frightening Revenant: The Wolf reveals horrific \nmutilations, each revealing something about his deaths. His \nempty eyes are as cold and bottomless as the well he was \ndrowned in. His pelt is a patchwork of burns and skinned \nflesh. His belly is full of slashes and stitches. His growl is \na terrifying sound, grinding painfully from a chest full of \nheavy stones and broken bones. No NPCs will approach \nor fight the Wolf, being paralyzed by terror. Particularly \npowerful NPCs, at the Storyteller’s discretion, can ignore \nthis effect. When a Hunter acts against the Returning Wolf, \nthey suffer 1 Penalty for each action taken.\nGift - The Better to Eat You With: The Wolf can \nswallow his enemies whole, trapping them inside his belly \nand crushing them to death with the heavy stones the \ngrandmother sewed inside it. When the Returning Wolf \ninflicts 1 Wound, it can swallow the victim whole as an \nadditional effect. In the next action, the victim can only \ntry to free themselves. If they fail the Position Check, or if \nthey decide to stay in the belly of the Returning Wolf, they \nreceive 1 additional Wound.\n66</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am hell-bent on revenge on the human world. I \nam a revenant animated by undying acrimony for the softskinned creatures that invaded my woods and yet had the \naudacity to condemn me to death. My only goal now is to \nglut my endless hunger for human flesh and fear. I have a \nparticular hatred for children, the elderly, and Hunters, \nwhom I see as responsible for my many deaths.\nSpecial Agenda (Iskra the Young Wolf): I harbor \na deep hatred for this little pest. She is somewhat linked to \nmy pain. I want to swallow her and let her slowly die in my \nstomach.\nNote: Iskra the Y oung Wolf is one of the Hunters featured \nin The Broken Ones expansion book.\nSpecial Agenda (Garou the Old Wolf): I want to warn \nthe poor fool so that he understands what he will face if he \nkeeps by the side of these blasted humans.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"cGIgGDGVf8r674SG","name":"The King’s Unlikely Tailor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"DVEOjAELLWmAM4rk","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The King’s Unlikely Tailor","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an anemic young man with a body covered in scars, escorted \nand aided by my rich friend who considers me his most precious possession.\n1 Wound</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 67","positive":"I am an anemic young man with a body covered in scars, escorted \nand aided by my rich friend who considers me his most precious possession.\n1 Wound","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The King’s Unlikely Tailor","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CnlKFEqLyde08zGT","name":"Gift - Soul Tailor","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The King’s Unlikely Tailor","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A suit sewn by the tailor masks the \nsoul so well that whoever wears it looks like another \nperson. They are seen as admirable and good, even while \ncommitting atrocious acts. Only children and the innocents \ncan see beyond the illusion. A Hunter can perform a \nDefense Check against an Opposition Level Hard 7 to see \nbeyond the deception of Soul Tailor.\nThe Cheating Friend</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 67","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The King’s Unlikely Tailor","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KyXtgFjOwGahOD7g","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The King’s Unlikely Tailor","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The King’s Unlikely Tailor\nInspired by The Emperor’s New Clothes (Neutral)\nDark Presence by Guido Campanini\nOnce upon a time, there was a young provincial tailor with the gift of knowing \nhow to see into people’s souls in order to dress them in the best possible manner. \nOne day his best friend convinced him to sew a suit for a wealthy merchant. To \ncover the wolfish soul of the greedy merchant, the poor tailor had to use his own \nsoul, one of a lamb, mixing his own blood in the dyes. It was a resounding success \nand the rumor spread all over Paris. The more his wealthy clientele grew thanks \nto the rumors spread by his friend, the more blood the poor tailor had to shed. \nHis success led him to the King’s court, where the young tailor began to kidnap \ninnocents from all over Paris to bleed them in his workshops. It was a necessary \nstep to manufacture dyes capable of disguising those with souls so corrupt. When \nthe King asked for a suit, the young tailor immediately realized that simple blood \nwould not be enough to conceal all the man had done to make his people suffer.\nDescriptor: I am an anemic young man with a body covered in scars, escorted \nand aided by my rich friend who considers me his most precious possession.\n1 Wound\nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: Finding the purest-hearted person in the nation to make a suit for \nthe King / I fell madly in love with the one person who never asked me for a \ndress, the King’s youngest daughter. I wouldn’t spill a drop for her dress, she is \ntoo pure. But I know that if I can’t find anyone for her father’s suit, I’ll have to \nuse her.\n67\nGift - Soul Tailor: A suit sewn by the tailor masks the \nsoul so well that whoever wears it looks like another \nperson. They are seen as admirable and good, even while \ncommitting atrocious acts. Only children and the innocents \ncan see beyond the illusion. A Hunter can perform a \nDefense Check against an Opposition Level Hard 7 to see \nbeyond the deception of Soul Tailor.\nThe Cheating Friend\nDescriptor: I am the young tailor’s “best” friend and, to \nkeep my life comfortable, I am willing to do anything. When \nI act for my own benefit, no one can stop me.\n1 Wound\nOpposition Level: Hard 7\nAgenda: Keep the tailor alive, become richer and richer, \nand to use his favor to ask for the hand of the King’s daughter.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 67","owner":"The King’s Unlikely Tailor","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-king-s-unlikely-tailor-67","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":67}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The King’s Unlikely Tailor\nInspired by The Emperor’s New Clothes (Neutral)\nDark Presence by Guido Campanini\nOnce upon a time, there was a young provincial tailor with the gift of knowing \nhow to see into people’s souls in order to dress them in the best possible manner. \nOne day his best friend convinced him to sew a suit for a wealthy merchant. To \ncover the wolfish soul of the greedy merchant, the poor tailor had to use his own \nsoul, one of a lamb, mixing his own blood in the dyes. It was a resounding success \nand the rumor spread all over Paris. The more his wealthy clientele grew thanks \nto the rumors spread by his friend, the more blood the poor tailor had to shed. \nHis success led him to the King’s court, where the young tailor began to kidnap \ninnocents from all over Paris to bleed them in his workshops. It was a necessary \nstep to manufacture dyes capable of disguising those with souls so corrupt. When \nthe King asked for a suit, the young tailor immediately realized that simple blood \nwould not be enough to conceal all the man had done to make his people suffer.\nDescriptor: I am an anemic young man with a body covered in scars, escorted \nand aided by my rich friend who considers me his most precious possession.\n1 Wound\nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: Finding the purest-hearted person in the nation to make a suit for \nthe King / I fell madly in love with the one person who never asked me for a \ndress, the King’s youngest daughter. I wouldn’t spill a drop for her dress, she is \ntoo pure. But I know that if I can’t find anyone for her father’s suit, I’ll have to \nuse her.\n67\nGift - Soul Tailor: A suit sewn by the tailor masks the \nsoul so well that whoever wears it looks like another \nperson. They are seen as admirable and good, even while \ncommitting atrocious acts. Only children and the innocents \ncan see beyond the illusion. A Hunter can perform a \nDefense Check against an Opposition Level Hard 7 to see \nbeyond the deception of Soul Tailor.\nThe Cheating Friend\nDescriptor: I am the young tailor’s “best” friend and, to \nkeep my life comfortable, I am willing to do anything. When \nI act for my own benefit, no one can stop me.\n1 Wound\nOpposition Level: Hard 7\nAgenda: Keep the tailor alive, become richer and richer, \nand to use his favor to ask for the hand of the King’s daughter.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Finding the purest-hearted person in the nation to make a suit for \nthe King / I fell madly in love with the one person who never asked me for a \ndress, the King’s youngest daughter. I wouldn’t spill a drop for her dress, she is \ntoo pure. But I know that if I can’t find anyone for her father’s suit, I’ll have to \nuse her.\n67","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"4tZqNmu7QmDO8bgT","name":"The Mothers of Fate","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"AI8uA6kLhMsUOIF8","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Mothers of Fate","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are three sisters, we never show our real \nidentity, but we twist fate to our pleasure thanks to our \npowerful magic.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 68","positive":"We are three sisters, we never show our real \nidentity, but we twist fate to our pleasure thanks to our \npowerful magic.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Mothers of Fate","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dkWb3l5EqIhe79VX","name":"Gift - The Way Forward","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Mothers of Fate","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The knowledge of the three \nsisters is absolute and unlimited; they know the past, \npresent, and future. By asking the Mothers of Fate for \nadvice or information, you will be able to obtain guidance \nto follow to achieve your goals or information that few \nknow. This all comes at a high price. Once per Session you \ncan ask the Storyteller a direct question about a person, a \nplace, or a secret, to which they will answer in detail and \nwith specifics. In exchange, the Hunter must perform a task \nfor the Mothers, but which the Hunter will not remember. \nThe Hunter receives 1 Pact Token, which the Storyteller can \nspend during a Scene to introduce the effects of the action \nthe Hunter performed for the Mothers. The action can \nbe anything, even in open contrast to the Hunter’s moral \nstances. They will be aware of what they have done only \nwhen the truth is revealed.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 68","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Mothers of Fate","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bXunzAFGMBDk0P3A","name":"Gift - As if by Magic","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Mothers of Fate","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The power of the Mothers of \nFate is such that it can change reality for a short period \nof time. By unconditionally accepting a request from the \nMothers of Fate and spending 1 Soma, once per Session, \nthe Hunter can ask the Mothers to modify the surrounding \nenvironment, adding or removing any object, creating an \nadvantage for themselves or whoever they wish.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 68","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Mothers of Fate","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"g46YQjaZ4naBW8xS","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Mothers of Fate","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Mothers of Fate\nInspired by the Fairy Godmothers of many \nfairytales (Ally)\nDark Presence by Francesco Panitti\nCloris, Panis, and Galis, called the Mothers of Fate. Since the \ndawn of time, there have been figures who control people’s \ndestiny, plot in the shadows, and hide in plain sight. They are \nthe ones we go to for advice and whom we trust blindly.\nThey use their proximity to manipulate people, enjoying their \nintrigues and rejoicing when everything goes according to \ntheir plans.\nThese figures are always represented as three sisters who, since \nancient times, have been weaving and cutting the threads of \neveryone’s destiny. Their true identity is unknown as they \nhave always hidden behind the name of Fairy Godmothers.\nWhen the three sisters insinuate themselves into the stories \nthey wove, they always did so by changing their appearance \nand name, all to get closer to the protagonists and manipulate \nthem according to their will. Some rumors say that it is \npossible to make deals with them, but always at a very high \nprice.\nDescriptor: We are three sisters, we never show our real \nidentity, but we twist fate to our pleasure thanks to our \npowerful magic.\n3 Wounds [1 for each Mother]\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\n68\nAgenda: Pretending to be friendly and kind, while \nmanipulating others’ choices according to our will / Appearing \nout of nowhere in time of need, thanks to our magic.\nGift - The Way Forward: The knowledge of the three \nsisters is absolute and unlimited; they know the past, \npresent, and future. By asking the Mothers of Fate for \nadvice or information, you will be able to obtain guidance \nto follow to achieve your goals or information that few \nknow. This all comes at a high price. Once per Session you \ncan ask the Storyteller a direct question about a person, a \nplace, or a secret, to which they will answer in detail and \nwith specifics. In exchange, the Hunter must perform a task \nfor the Mothers, but which the Hunter will not remember. \nThe Hunter receives 1 Pact Token, which the Storyteller can \nspend during a Scene to introduce the effects of the action \nthe Hunter performed for the Mothers. The action can \nbe anything, even in open contrast to the Hunter’s moral \nstances. They will be aware of what they have done only \nwhen the truth is revealed.\nGift - As if by Magic: The power of the Mothers of \nFate is such that it can change reality for a short period \nof time. By unconditionally accepting a request from the \nMothers of Fate and spending 1 Soma, once per Session, \nthe Hunter can ask the Mothers to modify the surrounding \nenvironment, adding or removing any object, creating an \nadvantage for themselves or whoever they wish.</p>","notes":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 68","owner":"The Mothers of Fate","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"core-book-the-mothers-of-fate-68","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":68}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Mothers of Fate\nInspired by the Fairy Godmothers of many \nfairytales (Ally)\nDark Presence by Francesco Panitti\nCloris, Panis, and Galis, called the Mothers of Fate. Since the \ndawn of time, there have been figures who control people’s \ndestiny, plot in the shadows, and hide in plain sight. They are \nthe ones we go to for advice and whom we trust blindly.\nThey use their proximity to manipulate people, enjoying their \nintrigues and rejoicing when everything goes according to \ntheir plans.\nThese figures are always represented as three sisters who, since \nancient times, have been weaving and cutting the threads of \neveryone’s destiny. Their true identity is unknown as they \nhave always hidden behind the name of Fairy Godmothers.\nWhen the three sisters insinuate themselves into the stories \nthey wove, they always did so by changing their appearance \nand name, all to get closer to the protagonists and manipulate \nthem according to their will. Some rumors say that it is \npossible to make deals with them, but always at a very high \nprice.\nDescriptor: We are three sisters, we never show our real \nidentity, but we twist fate to our pleasure thanks to our \npowerful magic.\n3 Wounds [1 for each Mother]\nOpposition Level: Medium 5\n68\nAgenda: Pretending to be friendly and kind, while \nmanipulating others’ choices according to our will / Appearing \nout of nowhere in time of need, thanks to our magic.\nGift - The Way Forward: The knowledge of the three \nsisters is absolute and unlimited; they know the past, \npresent, and future. By asking the Mothers of Fate for \nadvice or information, you will be able to obtain guidance \nto follow to achieve your goals or information that few \nknow. This all comes at a high price. Once per Session you \ncan ask the Storyteller a direct question about a person, a \nplace, or a secret, to which they will answer in detail and \nwith specifics. In exchange, the Hunter must perform a task \nfor the Mothers, but which the Hunter will not remember. \nThe Hunter receives 1 Pact Token, which the Storyteller can \nspend during a Scene to introduce the effects of the action \nthe Hunter performed for the Mothers. The action can \nbe anything, even in open contrast to the Hunter’s moral \nstances. They will be aware of what they have done only \nwhen the truth is revealed.\nGift - As if by Magic: The power of the Mothers of \nFate is such that it can change reality for a short period \nof time. By unconditionally accepting a request from the \nMothers of Fate and spending 1 Soma, once per Session, \nthe Hunter can ask the Mothers to modify the surrounding \nenvironment, adding or removing any object, creating an \nadvantage for themselves or whoever they wish.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Pretending to be friendly and kind, while \nmanipulating others’ choices according to our will / Appearing \nout of nowhere in time of need, thanks to our magic.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556804732,"modifiedTime":1781556804732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
